title: lemon crinkles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Blend in lemon rind.
Blend dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls and dip tops in granulated sugar.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Gently beat in dry ingredients just until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into a well-greased, lightly floured 2-quart swirl shaped small-tune baking pan.
(Editor's Note:
Does anyone really own a pan fitting this description?)
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Loosen sides of cake from pan and turn out on wire rack to cool.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: grandmama's pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions (either layer cake or sheet cake).
Combine rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until mixture thickens (usually 10 minutes).
Pour over cake.

title: beef in wine
directions: Cover meat with soup and wine.
Cook for 3 hours at 325°.

title: linguine casserole
directions: Cook linguine according to package.
Melt margarine in
medium saucepan over low.
Add flour and salt, stirring; add milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add liquid from mushrooms, water and cube.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly and slightly thick.
Add 2 cups sauce and mushrooms to linguine; toss until well mixed.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mocha walnut christmas cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water, 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth; cool to room temperature. In a small cup, dissolve instant coffee in boiling water; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and coffee; beat until creamy.
Add egg and melted morsels; mix well. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheets; cool completely.
Makes about 24 three-inch cookies.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Arrange spinach and strawberries on individual serving plates. Combine sugar, onion, paprika and Worcestershire sauce in a blender or food processor.
With machine running, add the vegetable oil and vinegar in a slow steady stream until thoroughly mixed and thickened.
Stir seeds in by hand.
Drizzle dressing over spinach and strawberries.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked apricots
directions: Pour half of the butter in the bottom of casserole dish, then half the crackers, half of the apricots and half of the sugar. Repeat in layers. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Remove from heat and add tea bags. Steam for 6 minutes in covered saucepan.
Remove tea bags and add cinnamon sticks and cloves.
(You can place these in a cheesecloth bag; optional.)
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Remove spices and add jello.
Stir and add juices and ReaLemon.
Stir well and let cool.
Let stand for 24 hours before serving.
Reheat to serve.

title: soy waffles
directions: Soak legumes 24 hours.
(A quantity of beans may be soaked, drained and frozen ahead of time.)
Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until very fine and light.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes on hot, sprayed waffle iron.
Serve with pureed fresh, frozen or canned fruit, sweetened as desired.

title: pancakes
directions: Whisk ingredients.
Drop 3 tablespoons on hot griddle.
Flip when bubbles appear.
Makes 9 pancakes.

title: celestial chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, mushrooms, pecans and crumbled bacon in larger bowl. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and sour cream. Add chicken to mixture, tossing lightly. Chill thoroughly. Serve in crisp lettuce cups. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sponge cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Make hole in center and add oil, egg yolks, flavor and water.
Mix in mixer until smooth. Beat egg whites very stiff. Pour batter mix over egg whites and mix gently.
Bake in ungreased tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°, then 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn upside-down to cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 7-inch pan.
Add ingredients in the order given (in layers).
Do not mix ingredients.
Do not remove cake from pan the first day or it will crumble.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: weight watcher chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender with skin removed.
Chop meat.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Chill.

title: goulash
directions: In a large, heavy pot, brown meat in shortening.
Add onion, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring the meat. Add enough water to cover the meat.
Add the bouillon cubes, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour, covered.
Add the tomatoes, green pepper and potato.
Simmer 45 minutes longer.
Add the cabbage and wine, if desired.
Check for seasoning.
Make a paste of cold water and cornstarch, stirring into the goulash. Simmer just until cabbage is tender and stew is thickened.
Makes 10 hearty servings.
Freezes well.

title: egg casserole(serves 9 to 12 people)
directions: Put grated cheese into lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cut margarine into slices and dot top of cheese.
Mix together half and half, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour half of this over cheese in pan.
Whip 12 eggs and pour over everything.
Pour remaining half and half mixture over eggs.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: olive cheese nuggets
directions: Blend together the cheese and butter.
Using your hands, mix in the flour and paprika to form a soft dough.
Shape dough around olives in thin layer.
Make sure it sticks.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and bake in preheated 400° oven until golden brown (15 minutes).
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in skillet and brown pork chops. Arrange chops on rice and cover with onions, tomatoes and green peppers.
Pour broth over everything and cover pan with foil. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: speedy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar; press down with fork.
Bake in 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet until brown.

title: rice lasagna
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Brown ground meat, onion and pepper; drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Beat egg slightly, stir in cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Coat 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam.
Spread 1/2 meat sauce on bottom. Spoon 1/2 rice over sauce.
Top with 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: luscious corn bread
directions: Put stick of margarine in 8-inch square pan and place in oven to melt while oven is preheating to 400°.
Beat egg and add other ingredients.
Blend well.
When margarine is just melted, add to egg mixture and thoroughly combine.
Pour back into pan in which margarine was melted.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix and add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Put peaches over batter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour juice over this and bake until brown in a 360° oven until golden brown.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft ball stage.
Add dates and cook until dates are dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts; cool. Beat until creamy enough to handle with hands.
Butter hands and pat into a smooth ball.
Make a roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in oiled or waxed paper until ready to use, then cut in 1/2 inch slices.

title: strawberry salad
directions: To jello, add water.
Dissolve and set aside 1/4 cup of mixture.
Add crushed pineapple and strawberries.
Mix well.
Set in refrigerator to congeal.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese with 1/4 cup jello mix.
Spread on top of jello and sprinkle with nuts.

title: bean salad
directions: Marinate for 24 hours.

title: pasta and beans casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; add seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: birdie's beans and bread
directions: Use casserole dish of desired size.
Crumble corn bread over bottom of bowl.
Add 1 to 2 cans of pinto beans.
Use enough juice to moisten corn bread slightly.
Cover with chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix 3/4 cup mayonnaise and dill pickle juice.
Pour over salad and poke holes to let dressing get to corn bread. Cover with diced tomatoes and crumbled bacon.

title: cinnamon pecans
directions: Heat pecan halves for 15 minutes at 200°; set aside.
Cook sugar, water, cinnamon and salt in heavy saucepan without stirring to 236°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and pecan halves.
Stir gently until nuts are well coated and mix looks glossy.
Turn out on well greased cookie sheet and separate using 2 forks.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine everything but sour cream.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Cool and add sour cream.
Pour in crust and chill.

title: best carrot cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; beat well. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.

Add to sugar mixture, stirring well. Add carrots, walnuts, pineapple (drained) and coconut. Stir well. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Pour Buttermilk Glaze over warm cake layers.
Let cool in pans 15 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks or paper towels, sifted with powdered sugar.
(This cake is very delicate and must be handled carefully.)
When completely cool, spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place bread in dish.
Add meat.
Mix all other ingredients as follows:
Beat eggs until fluffy; add seasoning and milk.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
Pour in dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Will puff, then fall a little after removing from oven. Make half for a small family.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Have cheese and butter or margarine at room temperature.
Mix thoroughly, then add other ingredients to make smooth dough.
Add Rice Krispies last.
Pinch off small balls and flatten with a fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Drain the cherries from the jar, reserving the juice. Combine 1 Tbsp. arrowroot or cornstarch with 1/4 c. of the cherry juice.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in small amount of water; strip meat from bones and chop into chunks.
Blend all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: marinated chicken italiano
directions: In shallow dish, pour dressing over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken, reserving marinade.
Grill or broil, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade, until done. Makes about 4 servings.

title: never fail hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water.
Add salt, sugar and Crisco with enough flour to handle the dough like biscuits.
Let dough rise in container until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Roll and cut out and dip rolls in melted shortening or margarine and fold. Let rise again.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: chili and then some(abundance and goodness)
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans; blend well.
Bring to boil and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add beans; simmer 15 minutes longer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: jo~anne's italian roast beef
directions: Layer as listed in a crock-pot. Cook on low for 8 hours. Serve on sub rolls with Swiss cheese and spicy brown mustard.

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: cherry pie
directions: *Use about 1/2 of the juice only.

title: kid's graham crunchies
directions: Spray a large cookie sheet with Pam.
Line with graham crackers. Break into pieces to cover entire bottom of sheet. Place butter or margarine in saucepan with brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add chopped nuts.
Pour mixture evenly over crackers.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix mustard, salt, 3/4 of sugar and onion in a blender. Alternate remainder of sugar with oil and vinegar with blender running.
When oil and vinegar are thoroughly mixed, add celery seed.

title: franks in hot sauce
directions: Cook ingredients 10 minutes.
Cut franks in 1-inch long pieces.
Add to sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 1 cup. Serve hot.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook raw peanuts, Milnot, sugar and Karo syrup until it forms a soft ball, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add red food coloring, oleo and powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper.

title: bleenies
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Add flour to pancake-like consistency.
Drop slowly into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: jim stack's chili
directions: Cook pork in a fry pan until done.
Remove fat.
Add chili mix, then add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Simmer 3 to 5 hours. Add chili powder to taste.
Stir frequently.
Makes enough for 4 to 6 people.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet (nonstick or brown paper covered).
Preheat oven to 350°. Put cookies in oven and immediately turn off heat.
Leave oven closed overnight (don't peek).
Store in airtight container. Makes 35 cookies.

title: smoked sausage with cabbage and potatoes
directions: Cut sausage into slices; set aside.
In a skillet, over medium heat, cook onions until tender.
Add sausage and potatoes; continue cooking until potatoes are tender, may be lightly browned.
Remove core from cabbage and cut into bite-size pieces, but not too small. Add about 1/3 of cabbage to skillet; adding a little salt and pepper.
Cook until cabbage becomes a little tender, turning often so potatoes and sausage do not burn.
Move 1/2 skillet mixture to large pot to make room for rest of cabbage.
Continue cooking until tender, removing part of mixture from skillet to pot until all of cabbage is cooked.
Heat cabbage and sausage mixture in pot until hot.
Serves 4.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in large bowl.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add oil and milk and add to mixture.
Keeps in covered container in refrigerator for up to six weeks.
Use as needed and bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 15 minutes. Fill tin 3/4 full.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: Mix together and make into ball or log.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, pineapple, onion and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill until firm enough to form into ball.
Roll ball in finely chopped walnuts.
Chill until ready to serve.
Best served with unsalted crackers.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook ground beef in big pot until brown and cooked all the way through.
Drain grease.
Add chopped onion and garlic, then put can of whole tomatoes in.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the chili beans, jalapeno and tomato sauce, then add the salt and pepper.
Lastly, add chili pepper to taste.
Let cook until boiling, then 30 minutes more.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwavable casserole. Microwave on High, 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumber is crisp-tender and onion translucent.
Ladle into a glass jar (rinsed with hot water to prevent cracking).
Cover; cool slightly and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, minus 1/2 cup water.
Add pineapple, juice and oranges.
Chill.
Blend powdered pudding in Cool Whip.
Spread over Jell-O.
Serve.

title: wild string bean casserole
directions: Arrange
all ingredients in layers.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter
and milk in cracker crumbs to right consistency to sprinkle on.
To this, add sharp Cheddar cheese and put on top of beans.
Bake
for
1 hour (or less) in a 350° oven.
Serves 10 or more people.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Place margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High until melted.
Stir in seeds.
Scrub potatoes, but do not peel. Cut into quarters and toss in margarine mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes (less potatoes less time), stirring midway through.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with vinegar and parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: frosty winter bars
directions: Line pan with half of crackers.
Combine butter, sugar, milk and egg; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, coconut and crumbs.
Spread over crackers in pan and cover with another layer of whole crackers.
Frost.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut florets; mix all ingredients together, using enough dressing to coat well.
Keep some bacon bits to sprinkle on top. Refrigerate.

title: alice's banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding mix and 4 cups milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers with pudding.

title: tuna puffs
directions: Add egg yolks in bread and tuna.
Beat egg whites and fold into soup.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pork patties
directions: Cook rice; cool. Thoroughly mix all ingredients, except tomato juice. Form into 12 patties and place in greased pan. Pour tomato juice over patties. Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 1 hour and 30 minutes more. Tomato juice will be absorbed.

title: mommy's flour dough
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add shortening and cold water. Don't knead!
Mix with fork, then hands.
Great for apple, peach and pumpkin pies.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk.
Add egg yolks; stir until blended well together.
Pour into chilled pie crust or graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites and add sugar.
Put on top of pie and brown slightly.
Then place in refrigerator.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Mix your wet ingredients together first, then toss everything together.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans with butter in oven.
Mix milk, water and vanilla.
Put in ice cream churn and freeze.
Add cooled pecans to ice cream when it starts to freeze.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and stuffing mix in turkey broth about 10 minutes.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Brown sausage and drain.
Add sausage, onion and celery to bread mixture along with eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut egg in halves.
Slip out yolks.
Mash with fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Refill white with yolk mixture.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and other dry ingredients.
Sift three times.
Stir in raisins.
Combine remaining wet ingredients together.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture and mix until moistened.
Pour into greased (bottom and sides) pan.
Use a large bread pan or a 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to one hour.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In a large skillet melt margarine over medium heat.
Saute onions and green onions until onions are clear.
Add lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic and cook for 10 more minutes.
Add shrimp, salt and cayenne pepper; stir well.
Reduce heat to low and cover to simmer for about 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Saute garlic (minced) and onion (chopped) in butter. Add 1 1/2 cups whipping cream to butter mixture and over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring until cream thickens.
Add the drained and cooked fettucine pasta and the remaining cream.
Toss in the cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apples and cranberries.
Put in buttered casserole.
Pour sugar over fruit mixture.
In another bowl, mix oats, sugar, butter and flour.
Sprinkle on top of fruit mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: white lemon fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, beaten 1 at a time. Add flour a little at a time, then add flavoring, nuts and raisins.
Place in a greased and floured tube pan; bake at 250° to 275° for 2 hours, until light brown.
Makes a big cake.
Good for the holidays.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix flour, sugar and slightly beaten egg yellows together.
Add milk and cool over very low heat or double boiler until it slightly sticks to the spoon or becomes a little thicker, stirring constantly.
Beat egg whites, adding a little sugar (about 1/4 cup) until stiff.
Remove other mixture from heat; add egg whites and whip them in.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Cool in refrigerator. Stir before serving.

title: amy's krispie treats
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Pat in buttered cake pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: cranberry sour cream mold
directions: Mix Jell-O and water together.
Chill to consistency of egg whites.
Fold into marble whole cranberry sauce and sour cream. Pour into mold which has been lightly greased with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, blend the soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper; stir in green beans.
Cover with wax paper. Cook in a microwave oven for eight minutes or until hot, stirring two times.
Top with onions and cook, uncovered, for two or three minutes.

title: healthy pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter with sugar; add syrup.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat in vanilla and flour.
Stir in pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until golden.

title: mrs. harold gillis' nut loaf
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks and beat well. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add to mixture, alternating with milk and flavoring.
Add nuts and stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix together, then add wings.
Marinate at least 24 hours, 48 hours is better.
Stir once or twice a day.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam and lay wings out on it and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
I turn them about halfway through.

title: claud's carrots
directions: Peel and quarter lengthwise the carrots.
Cook in saucepan with small amount of water (to steam) and sugar, nutmeg, ginger and butter.
Cook until tender.

title: heavenly four layer dessert
directions: Mix and press first three ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls into greased skillet & fry. Drain on towel.

title: broccoli and carrot bake
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, spray with Pam.
Put in veggies, add Cheddar cheese on top.
Mix mushroom soup with skim milk, pour on top and add cereal.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 1 minute fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add other ingredients, stirring over low heat until sugar is melted. Bring to boil; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir until creamy enough to spread.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic 3 minutes.
Add remaining scampi ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add fettucini; toss and heat through.

title: veg-beef soup
directions: Add all ingredients to large pot.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Also good the second day.

title: spareribs and potatoes in hoisin sauce
directions: Have spareribs cut Chinese style 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Pare potatoes and cube as for stew.
Brown spareribs; add potatoes, salt, hoisin sauce, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 25 minutes.
(Add more water if necessary.)
Gravy will be made by itself without thickening.
Serve with rice.

title: grandpa antle's sweet potatoes
directions: Will need salt and pepper shakers.

title: turkey hot dish
directions: Cook celery in water for 5 minutes and drain.
Crush crackers. Put half in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and milk and warm.
Add turkey, onion, peas, nuts and cheese on top of crackers.
Put all the rest of the crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Good way to use left over turkey.

title: mrs. rowe's grape butter
directions: Boil grapes and sugar together for 20 minutes.
Rub through a sieve.
Boil again for 10 minutes.
Skim, then bottle and seal.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Put pork roast into a heavy pan.
Combine tomatoes, vinegar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Pour over meat, cover and bake 5 hours at 300°.

title: spinach beef biscuit bake
directions: Press and flatten biscuits onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside. In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. In a bowl, beat eggs. Add spinach and mushrooms; mix well. Stir in the cheeses, garlic powder, salt, pepper and beef mixture; mix well. Spoon into prepared crust. Drizzle with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is lightly browned. Yield: 6 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put cereal in a brown bag.
Shake with powdered sugar.
In a pan, melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Put cereal in a large bowl and pour mixture over it.
After cooled, pour 1 cup of powdered sugar over it and mix.

title: nana burke's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Use cookie press to create neat shapes for all occasions.

title: escalloped sweet potatoes
directions: Pare and slice potatoes.
Use a wok or heavy iron skillet. Put layer of potatoes, then a layer of apple slices.
Repeat layers of potatoes, apple, sugar and butter until finished.
Add water.
Cover tightly.
Cook 30 to 60 minutes, until apples are soft and mushy.

title: easy confetti-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Rinse with cold water. Drain again. Layer half each of pasta and next 8 ingredients in large (2 1/2-quart) bowl. Drizzle with half of salad dressing. Repeat layering with remaining ingredients. Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Toss gently before serving, if desired. Yields 10 to 12 servings. Actually up to 20. Serves 20. Must do ahead.

title: reuben sandwich i
directions: Spread each slice of bread with thousand island dressing.
Top 4 of the bread slices with sauerkraut, cheese and pastrami.
Place remaining bread slices on sandwich.
Spread margarine on the outside of each sandwich.
Heat a large skillet over medium high heat.
Grill until browned, then turn and grill until heated through, and cheese is melted.

title: shrimp sauce and rice
directions: Wash shrimp well.
Cover with water; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Drain shrimp, reserving liquid. Let shrimp cool.
Meanwhile, add 1 can of tomato sauce to juice and remaining ingredients.
Cut up shrimp.
Add into juice. Simmer until ingredients are soft.
Cook 1 cup rice.
Drain dry. Serve with shrimp sauce.

title: toll house walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in sugar.
Beat in brown sugar and beat in flour.
Add butter.
Beat well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: apricot and apple cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add balance of ingredients to mixture.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: ginny's onion breads
directions: Slice French bread to 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange flat onto cookie sheet; set aside.

title: feather cake
directions: First, cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Then add sweet milk, sifted flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and yellow cake. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until a tester comes out clean.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls into melted chocolate.

title: bakers bunch bread(to make with your kids.)
directions: Note:
This recipe is an easy mixing method which also allows for slow rising in the refrigerator.
Children may prepare the dough one day, then bake the next.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Blend sugar with oil.
Mix together 1/2 cup hot water with cocoa powder; add to first mixture.
Add baking soda to sour milk (add 1 teaspoon vinegar to milk).
Add sifted flour and salt alternately with sour milk to first mixture, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 (9 x 13 x 2-inch) cake.

title: vegetable saute
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add vegetables; cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle salad dressing mix over vegetables.
Toss to coat well.
Stir in vinegar until well mixed.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bob's scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter and drain the whole kernel corn.
Beat the eggs. Combine all the ingredients together, adding the muffin mix last. Pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Good with ham or pork chops.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in pan.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat (low) and simmer 5 minutes.
Prepare rice, serve mixture over rice.
Top with garnishes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix. Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Press mixture in ungreased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until brown.
Cut in squares while warm.
Cool before removing.

title: goat cheese calzone
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except dough and oil.
Spoon filling onto 1/2 of dough circle within 1 inch of edge.
Moisten edge with water; fold dough over the filling to make edges meet.
Roll edges to seal. Brush dough with olive oil.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 375°; bake 10 to 15 minutes more, or until golden brown.
Yields 1 large Calzone, enough for 2 generous portions.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese in blender.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Top with Doritos and cheese.
Bake until heated at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Have very cool, then shred.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Mix rest of ingredients for dressing.
Then fold into potato mixture.
Chopped ham may be added.

title: crumb topped asparagus
directions: Break 1 slice of bread into 6 pieces and drop into blender. Cover and run on speed 4 (or low) until bread is finely crumbed. Empty into a 1 cup measure.
Repeat process with remaining bread until you have 1 cup crumbs; set aside.
Put eggs in blender. Cover and run on speed 4 (or low) until finely chopped.
Melt butter in frypan; add bread crumbs, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until crumbs are golden brown.
Stir in chopped eggs.
Serve hot over hot cooked asparagus. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Soften the instant chopped onion into the milk.
Add the rest of ingredients together.
Mix all together.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven in an 8-inch pan.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix well Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients in order as listed and mix well.
Put into refrigerator to cool.
Best after 24 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut green peppers in half, removing core and seeds.
Place peppers in 2-quart (12 x 7-inch) baking dish.
In medium mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients, using only half of the tomato sauce.
Spoon mixture into pepper halves.
Spoon remaining tomato sauce over the meat.
Cook, covered, with wax paper, 12 minutes or until meat is done.

title: individual pizzas
directions: Shape biscuits into 3 to 4-inch circles or can be placed between sheets of waxed paper, 1 at a time, and flattened.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Spread with tomato sauce or paste.
Add dash of Italian seasoning.
Sprinkle meat on sauce; top with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: bang
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/2 and arrange around a pie pan after putting in garlic and wine.
Put cheese in the middle.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chuck wagon potatoes
directions: Mix onion, pepper, cream of chicken soup, cheese and sour cream.
Combine with potatoes.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Crush cornflakes and mix with butter.
Sprinkle on top. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cover except for last 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mold dough into teaspoon size balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet about 10 minutes.
Let sit on hot sheet after removing.
Yum, Yum!

title: cabbage rolls with seasoned rice
directions: Bring a pot of water to boil.
Drop in the cabbage leaves and cook 3 minutes; drain.
In a skillet, cook the onion, stirring in a small amount of water over medium heat until limp, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in the nutmeg, salt, half of the tomato sauce and 1 cup rice.
Divide the rice mixture among the cabbage leaves; roll up and fasten with toothpicks.

title: chilies and sausage quiche
directions: Line bottom of pie shells with split and seeded whole green chilies. Sprinkle sausage over chilies. Combine eggs, cheeses and seasonings.
Pour over sausage. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden brown. Remove from oven and allow to set 5 minutes before serving. Serves 8.

title: do ahead breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of buttered 8 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with most of the cheese, then layer browned and drained sausage.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups of milk and dry mustard.
Pour mixture on top of sausage and sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, mix soup and milk; pour over top of casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon garlic chicken or veal
directions: Place cutlets in frying pan and add white wine, garlic, 2 tablespoons lemon juice and sprinkle with parsley.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes each side.
Serve with remaining lemon, cut in wedges.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda and salt in buttermilk.
Place fruit, nuts and candy in large bowl with flour.
Stir to coat each piece good.
Then, add to cream mixture.
Add coconut.
Dough will be stiff; mix by hand.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in tube or loaf pan.

title: vichyssoise(soup)
directions: Place
potatoes, leeks, celery and onions in a pan with 1 cup water.
Season and cook very slowly until soft.
Pour on the stock and bring to a boil.

title: cornbread and cabbage
directions: Chop the cabbage; cook until tender and drain.
Mix the cheeses with the soup and add drained cabbage, onion and pepper; place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with about 1-inch cornbread crumbs and the stick of margarine, sliced.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve in 2 hours.

title: mediterranean chicken(4 servings)
directions: In large skillet, lightly brown sausage; push to side.
Add chicken; brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and vegetables; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water. Stir into chicken mixture.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until heated through.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball onto surface dusted with Bisquick.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in Bisquick.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes, until soft and puffed.
Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes until golden.

title: frosty strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1 cup water. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Spoon in ice cream and stir until melted and smooth. Chill until thickened, about 20 minutes. Fold in strawberries.
Pour into pie shell. Chill until firm, approximately 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with Cool Whip and fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: hot chocolate malt(microwave)
directions: In 4 cup glass measure, combine all ingredients.
Cook on 70 for 5 to 6 minutes or until hot, stirring once during cooking time.
Serve in warm mugs.

title: fried tomatoes and ricethis recipe is adapted from a 19th century book of recipes.
directions: Cook the rice in cooking oil for 15 minutes. stirring frquently. In another pan pour in bacon drippings. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to the onions and continue to cook for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring often. Add hot water to the rice, a little at a time, until it reaches consistence of firm boiled rice. Add rice to the tomatoes and serve.

Serves 4 The original recipe read like this "Fry half a small cup of rice in hot lard 15 minutes. In another pan fry in drippings 1/4 of a small onion, not an El Paso onion, but a northern sized onion. Add 1/2 cup of tomato and let fry.

Add hot water to the rice until the consistency of firm boiled rice. Add a little at a time and put contents of the two pans together and serve in a hot dish with toast, if you like. Salt and pepper, of course."

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Buy noodles first, then you bake until it is soft.
Then you put some sauce on it.
Spicy stuff is in the sauce.
You put five spoonfuls of the spicy stuff in the sauce.
Put it in the microwave until it gets hot.
Then you
eat it!

title: layered ranchers dip
directions: On a deep dish pan, spread the beans.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, taco seasoning, mayonnaise, then spread on top of beans. Garnish with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rice-a-roni
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine. Add rice, spaghetti and onion. Cook and stir for 8 to 10 minutes or until spaghetti is golden brown. Add water and bouillon. Cover and simmer over low heat 25 to 30 minutes or until moisture is absorbed and spaghetti and rice are tender.
Serves 6 (3/4 cup each).

title: easy overnight bubble bread
directions: Generously butter a 9 X 13 inch baking pan. Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan. Place frozen dinner rolls in a single layer on top of pecans. Sprinkle dry pudding mix over the top. Combine butter and brown sugar in a small saucepan. Heat until boiling then pour over rolls. Cover with plastic wrap or wax paper and allow to stand overnight. In the morning, preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion slightly in butter; add ground meat.
Cover, but stir occasionally until meat is nicely browned.
Add beans, rinsed of their liquid and tomatoes.
Season with salt, pepper, sugar and chili powder to suit taste.
Cook mixture slowly for 1 hour, tightly covered.
Water may be added if too thick.
This is good cooked in a crock-pot also.

title: make and bake chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in a plastic bag to coat.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes per side.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
After this is well mixed, add 1 package of dry yeast that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Keep at least overnight before using.

title: potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut in half; do not peel.
Barely cover potatoes with boiling water.
Cook about 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain; cool slightly.
Strip off skins and cut potatoes into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes; turn into large bowl.
Add celery, red pepper, onions and pickles; toss together.

title: corned beef and cabbage salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water in small pan; dissolve over slow heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in onion, lemon juice and salt.
Gradually stir in mayonnaise.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 1-quart mold.
Top can be garnished with olives and pimiento.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter until soft. Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add all other ingredients, except flour and beat until smooth. Gradually add flour. Roll dough into small balls. Press flat with a fork on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 60 (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: aunt lily's health cookies
directions: Beat eggs and oil.
Add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and raisins or nutmeats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Store these in freezer as they mold easily. Excellent for diabetic's diet.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat juice from oranges.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Cool, then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Cut oranges into small pieces and add to gelatin mixture, then add nuts and coconut.
Stir all together gently and chill for several hours before serving.

title: szechuan noodles
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse, drain and set aside. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet; add pepper strips, onions and garlic. Saute 2 minutes. Stir in spinach; cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat; cool. Spoon mixture over pasta. Add chicken and chestnuts. Combine remaining oil and the rest of the ingredients; stir well and toss over pasta. Toss to coat. Serves 6.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until smooth.
Keeps for 1 month in refrigerator.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix well sugar, baking powder, flour and milk.
Pour this batter on melted butter; do not stir. Pour fruit over batter; do not stir.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
When using fresh blueberries, add a little vanilla.
Use 7 x 10-inch or 9 x 9-inch size dish.

title: cabbage head loaf
directions: Select a large loose leaf head of cabbage, wash and take apart keeping whole.
Keep the small center for the heart of the loaf. Parboil cabbage leaves in salt water a few minutes until it wilts. Drain in colander.

title: spinach patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into patties and brown in butter 2 minutes on each side.
Yields 12 patties.

title: church punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and freeze in 1/2 gallon milk cartons. When ready to serve, thaw enough to tear carton and break into slush in a bowl.
Add 1 quart well-chilled ginger ale to each 1/2 gallon fruit juice.
Yield:
Seventy 4 ounce servings or one hundred 3 ounce servings.

title: banana sour cream coffee cake
directions: In bowl, cream butter or margarine until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add mashed bananas, vanilla and dairy sour cream.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold into the creamed mixture, stirring just to blend.
In bowl, combine finely chopped nuts, 1/4 cup sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle half this mixture over bottom of well-greased Bundt pan, ring mold (6 1/2 cup) or tube pan.
Spoon in half the batter.
Sprinkle on remaining nut mixture and cover with balance of batter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until cake is nicely browned and starts to leave the sides of the pan.
Let cake cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Shake loose and turn out on rack to complete cooling.
Wrap well in foil to store.

title: wine drops
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add molasses.
Stir.
Add milk with dry ingredients, alternately, that have been sifted together.
Last add fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bubble pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain well and add pizza sauce and mushrooms. Stir well. Cut biscuits into small cubes. Add to mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Add cheeses and bake until cheese melts.

title: caramel turtle fudge cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick of melted margarine, oil, water, eggs and 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk in a bowl and mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13 pan and pour 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. During baking, melt caramels and other 1/2 of can of Eagle Brand milk in top of double boiler or microwave.
When completely melted, add pecans.
When cake is done, pour caramel mixture over top, then cover with remaining cake mixture and bake for 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: microwave tomatoes with brown sugar and bacon
directions: Salt and pepper the tomatoes lightly.
Top each tomato with 1 teaspoon butter and 2 teaspoons brown sugar.
Place each tomato in a custard cup, cut side up.
Place the cups around the outer edge of a plate, leaving a space between them.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with bacon and serve.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into buttered casserole dish.
Add butter, sugars, cinnamon and small amount of water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.
Check water and add more, if needed.

title: pastry wrapped olives
directions: In a large bowl combine pie crust prepared according to package directions, shredded cheese and bacon bits.
Pat dry the olives, shape about 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Makes 30.

title: punch
directions: Freeze all together, then add 1 (2 liter) bottle ginger ale. If you make double, add another bottle of ginger ale.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift the flour, salt and soda into a large bowl.
Add sugar, melted margarine, eggs, bananas and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove pan and cool.

title: 6-week muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.
(Let stand 8 hours before using.)
Use as desired.
Remove 1 tablespoon and place in coffee cup and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
May also be baked in the oven like regular muffins.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut, mix other ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and stir well.
Before serving, add 2 bananas, cut into rings.
Best if refrigerated several hous before serving.

title: wash-day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 11-inch pan.
Place drained fruit in pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over fruit.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (for 45 minutes if gas oven).

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients for crust and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the eggs, oleo and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Add the bananas and pineapple. Spread the Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.

title: oven baked italian bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Cut bread in half.
Spread over bread.
Layer sliced red onions and grated cheese on top. Wrap
in foil and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: patti's roast potatoes
directions: Put butter, oil, potatoes, onion and garlic into a 10 x 15-inch baking pan at least 2 inches deep.
Spread vegetables evenly.
Bake on bottom rack at 475° for 30 minutes.
Stir with wide spatula after 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt, spices, and sugar. Add oil, eggs, pumpkin, and water, beating until well blended. Stir in pecans. Pour batter into 2 lightly greased 9x5x3 loaf pans. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in the center of a loaf comes out clean. Remove from pan and cool on wire racks.

title: my mama's pecan pie
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining pecans on top. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Best to use shallow pie pans.)

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, dry ingredients and vanilla. Pour half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling, then remainder of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: wanda's original beanless chili
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Pour into large (5-quart) saucepan.
Add tomato juice and add spices and other ingredients. Bring to boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve. Will feed very large family.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
In a large skillet, place beans, tomato sauce, chopped tomatoes, mushrooms, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Now add browned meat and mix well.
Put on stove on low heat for 1 to 2 hours.
One-half hour before serving, add onion and bell pepper; cook until slightly soft.
Ready to eat!

title: fruit salad
directions: In saucepan, put vanilla pudding mix with pineapple juice. Bring to a boil and pour over fruit.
Chill and serve.
Double for large groups.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg.
Stir until butter is melted. Then add yeast mixture.
Stir in 3 cups self-rising flour until dough is gooey.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours (one night is best or 2 or 3 days is okay.)
Roll out dough on lightly floured board to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut and flip over in melted butter and place on a cookie sheet.
Let stand at least 1 hour in warm area, then bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown at 350°.

title: cocoa pie (chocolate)
directions: Blend flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in the top of a double boiler. Then add milk and cook about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Add egg yolks and 2 tablespoons butter. Return to heat and cook for 2 minutes. Stir constantly.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients into a batter.
Peel onions.
Slice and separate into rings.
Heat oil at least 1 inch deep.
Dip rings in batter and fry until done.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chips and white chocolate in large saucepan on low heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Decorate as desired.
Refrigerate until firm. Store at room temperature.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: caramel apple crisp
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Peel and slice apples. Layer them in glass dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Set aside.

title: hearty hamburger pie
directions: Combine beef with egg, salt, crumbs, cumin, garlic powder, mustard and herbs. Layer pie crust with potatoes, onion and mushrooms, leaving some mushrooms to encircle the pie.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cook a little longer if potatoes are not done.
Top with cheese and parsley when done. Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: traditional brisket
directions: Place brisket in a deep, rectangular pan.
Enclose the meat in tinfoil.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Place sliced onions on top of meat.
Cover and seal with tinfoil.
Cook approximately 2 hours at 350°.
Then take meat out and slice diagonally.
Put back into tinfoil.
Add beef broth and cover.
Bake another 2 hours. Meat should fall apart and be soft and tender when done.
If meat looks dry when baking, add water.

title: japanese fruit pies
directions: Melt margarine and let cool.
Then cream with sugar.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken breast delight
directions: Mix the dressing, preserves, onion mix and water.
Pour over chicken and cover; cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cover off and add pineapple for 10 minutes.
Also can use other chicken pieces.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening and add sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk, food coloring and vinegar. Pour into two greased 8-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lincoln almond cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar and butter.
Sift together flour and baking powder; slowly add to butter and sugar mixture alternately with small amount of milk.
Mix thoroughly. Add chopped almonds and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
In bowl, beat egg whites with salt until stiff; blend with other mixture.
Pour into greased and floured angel food pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool upside-down on a wire rack.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Form into 2 ounces tightly packed meat balls.
Bake in shallow pan 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: dump in cobbler
directions: Melt butter and dump in everything and bake at 350° until brown.

title: velvet almond fudge pie
directions: Prepare pie crust and set aside.
Chop almonds and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Blend together until smooth, pie filling mix, corn syrup, milk, egg and chocolate.
Add almonds and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until top is firm and begins to crack.
Cool at least 4 hours. Serve with whipped topping.

title: hot crab spread for crackers(appetizer)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Spread evenly in baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese to taste.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly and slightly browned. Serve hot or cold with crackers.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cream eggs, milk and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Melt butter and soak into bread cubes.
Pour into casserole dish, sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake approximately 45 minutes in 325° oven (do not cover).

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: In pan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple rings
directions: Mix flour, shortening and milk.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Sprinkle dough with cinnamon or spice.
Spread apples on dough.
Roll and slice.
Place in baking dish.
In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugars and water; bring to boil.
Pour over rolls. Bake until brown.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream.
Drop mixture, using a teaspoon. Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: quick pineapple dessert
directions: Mix well the pineapple and package of pistachio pudding.
Then add the other ingredients.
Stir well.
Refrigerate before serving.
Garnish with a cherry (optional).

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine shredded cheese, sugar and flour.
Mix well and spread over pineapple.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Finely chop stems and saute in butter with onions.
In a mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Adding bread crumbs to make mixture stiff enough to stay together.
Fill mushrooms to heaping.	Place in a baking dish and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 400 degrees until light brown.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set and top with chilled pie filling. Refrigerate leftovers, if any.

title: scrambled eggs with crabmeat and vermouth
directions: Break eggs into large mixing bowl and beat with whisk until well blended.
Heat half of butter in top of double boiler over simmering water.
Pour in eggs and stir with whisk until they just begin to set.
Stir in remaining butter and crabmeat and continue cooking for about 15 minutes or until eggs are creamy (do not overcook).
Remove pan from heat and stir in vermouth, salt and pepper.
Spoon eggs on serving plates and sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: dickie's chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into delicious sized squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cornbread
directions: On wax paper, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking powder and sugar.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly; add milk and beat until blended.
Beat in butter.
Add flour mixture and stir only until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Turn into a buttered pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve at once.

title: special k peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and let cook a few seconds.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Stir in Special K and coat all cereal.
Form into small balls; let cool on waxed paper or cookie sheet.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Grease bottom and sides of an 8 x8 inch pan.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; remove from heat.
Add sugar, vanilla, milk and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan, before cutting into bars. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: a dozen corn muffins
directions: Spray a large muffin pan with vegetable oil spray (butter flavored).
Mix ingredients together well in a large bowl.
Fill muffin pan cups 1/2 to 2/3 full of batter.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven until golden brown.

title: double lime punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Serve in punch cups.
Makes 10 servings.

title: dilled mayonnaise mustard
directions: In a blender, combine egg, mustard and salt and blend on high. Add vinegar and blend another few seconds.
Add olive oil in a thin stream, blending until all of the oil has been added.
Stir in dill.
Refrigerate until ready to use as a spicy mayonnaise/mustard.

title: waffles
directions: Mix together.
Pour batter into a waffle iron.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach to directions.
Drain and save liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat and add flour, stirring until blended and smooth but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, stirring frequently.
Add evaporated milk.
Cook and stir until smooth and thick, adding spinach liquor as needed to control consistency.
Add seasonings and cheese which has been cut up in small pieces, stirring until melted.
Combine with spinach.
May be served immediately or put in casserole and refrigerate overnight.

title: dream bars
directions: Cream together butter, 1/2 cup of the brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Pat out in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, while mixing the following:
Beat eggs, vanilla, salt, remaining 1 cup of brown sugar with 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour over baked crust.
Return to oven; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; cut into bars.

title: bulgoggi(from korea)
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Combine remaining ingredients. marinate steak in mixture for 1 hour or longer.
Saute in small amount of oil or cook over charcoal in a bulgoggi brazier. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: raspberry topped icebox cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with some of the graham crackers.
Pour cold milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended. Let stand for 5 minutes, then blend in Cool Whip.
Spread half of mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip mixture.
Spread raspberry pie filling over.
Chill about 3 hours.

title: mom butterscotch cookies(a dunking cookie)
directions: Mix and shape into 3 or 4 rolls; refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(We made them large.)
When cold, they get very hard; good dunking in milk, tea and coffee. Put in cookie jar; they get soft the older they are.
If any are left, can add apple to cookie jar.

title: fried bass meuniere
directions: Dredge the fish in a mixture of cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Fry slowly in margarine or cooking oil until browned. Remove the fish and garnish with parsley.
Stir the vinegar into the fat in which the fish were fried and pour this over the fish.

title: low calorie dip
directions: Blend all in a blender until smooth.
Refrigerate for a while before using to allow flavors to blend.

title: quick diabetic pickled beets
directions: Drain off one-half of beet liquid. Sprinkle sweetener, salt and pepper over beets. Add vinegar to cover. Cover and refrigerate.

title: marbled double chocolate cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, beat butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt until smooth.
Stir together flour and cocoa.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until a soft dough is formed. Press dough into bottom and 2-inches up sides of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/2 cup of sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.

title: fruit salsa
directions: Chop and combine kiwi, mandarin oranges and strawberries.
Add sugar to taste.
Serve with cinnamon tortilla chips.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil the chicken breasts and cube them.
Combine melted margarine and stuffing.
Put 1/2 mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer chicken, then mushrooms.
Combine soup, sour cream and broth and spread over layers.
Top with remaining stuffing mix and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour crushed pineapple over marshmallows.
Let stand 1 hour. Pour fruit cocktail over pineapple and marshmallows.
Using mixer, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Mix altogether and freeze.
May add maraschino cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain; place butter in casserole dish and let melt in oven.
Put broccoli in dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef over medium heat.
Drain in colander with beans.
Toss all ingredients together.
Serve immediately.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Orange jello and whip cream first, then mandarin oranges, crushed pineapple and cottage cheese.
Can be fixed with all nonfat ingredients.

title: chilies-egg puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, Jack cheese and butter.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in chilies. Pour mixture into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
(A partially baked pie crust could be used if you prefer.)
Bake for about 35 minutes or until top is browned and center appears firm.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 servings.
(One can of chilies makes a milder dish.) Picante sauce can be served to individual taste.

title: coconut carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Or leave in pan and put icing on when cake is completely cooled.
Ice with cream cheese frosting with toasted coconut on top.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: To slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour cold water in a bowl, sprinkle gelatine on top of water.
Add to hot pumpkin mixture.
Mix thoroughly and cool.
When it begins to thicken, add remaining sugar.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Put in cooked 9-inch pie shell.

title: zucchini - pineapple
directions: Peel zucchini and either cut into 1/2 inch cubes or shred. Mix zucchini with other ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes. Fill pint jars with the hot mixture and cooking liquid, leaving 1/2 inch headspace. Adjust lids and process in a waterbath for 15 minutes.

title: surprisin carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 round pans.
In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat next 4 ingredients.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until well mixed.
With spoon, stir in carrots and walnuts.
Turn into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove, cool, fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake crusts and fill with sweetened strawberries.
Combine in saucepan, water, sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 package of strawberry Jell-o. Cool and pour over fresh strawberries that have been sweetened to taste.
Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Wash breasts; place in broiler pan.
Mix sour cream, mushrooms (as many as you want), soup and wine together; pour over chicken. Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bon appetit!!

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in large pot; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 7 to 8 minutes.
Gradually stir 1/4 cup milk into flour, making a paste.
Stir into soup.
Add remaining 2 3/4 cups milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Makes approximately 9 cups.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter (1/4 cup).
Press into pie plate.
Cook onions in butter (1/4 cup), stirring to separate, until tender.
Press into cracker shell.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Lightly brown celery, onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.
Put cooked chicken on top before serving.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Coarsely crush cookies.
Mix with
margarine and spread over bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread over cookie layer.
After ice cream has frozen, cover it with a layer of thick fudge sauce.
Let that freeze and then cover with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
If desired, may drizzle chocolate sauce and chopped nuts over it.
Keep in freezer until a few minutes before serving.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and orange juice.
Then mix in wafer crumbs.
Pinch off in small pieces and make into balls.
Roll in coconut and refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 6 dozen balls.

title: family meat loaf
directions: Sprinkle meat with dry milk thoroughly.
Add other ingredients and mix well (mixture will be sticky).
Place in lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and red rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together all ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.
Continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ginger peanut chicken
directions: Remove skins from chicken.

Sprinkle chicken with salt and ground ginger. Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook chicken in hot oil, turning occasionally, until chicken is browned on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Transfer chicken to a plate, reserving pan drippings in skillet.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Prepare "rolled biscuits" as directed on Bisquick package. Separate dough into two equal parts.
Roll each part out fairly thick.
Place raw sausage on dough and roll up jelly roll style. Freeze about 10 minutes to simplify slicing.
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until brown on each side.
Serve with mustard.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Pour lemon juice on both sides and top with sliced onion.
Sprinkle sugar and Worcestershire on chops.
Top with catsup.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 375°.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and milk together over medium heat.
Drain corn and add to cream cheese mixture.
Add peppers if desired.
Pour into 2 quart casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Slice butter into pats and set over top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: pineapple sandwich
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add to the juice the well beaten egg plus sugar and flour.
Cook until thick.
Cool and add the pineapple and mayonnaise.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: strawberry and banana smoothie(makes 1 serving)
directions: Blend on high speed in blender until smooth and ice cubes are crushed.

title: blueberry cheesecake pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven; heat to 425°.

title: easy microwave lasagna
directions: Mix sauce, water and ground beef.
In a separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg and pepper (if you wish).
Make sure your pan fits into your microwave.
Layer sauce, noodles, cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers and then end with sauce on top.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes and then 50% power for 30 to 32 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes and serve.

title: cold banana bisque
directions: Put half and half and bananas in blender until thoroughly mixed and creamy.
Chill.
Place the diced bread in a buttered, shallow pan.
Mix with the butter and sugar mix.
Put in a 300° oven until lightly caramelized, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle cinnamon croutons on cold soup just before serving.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix
sugar and cornstarch;
combine with water, raisins and salt;
cook until thickened.
Add butter, lemon juice and extract. Cool slightly and pour into pastry lined pie pan and top with pastry,
plain
or
latticed.
Bake
at
450° for 10 minutes, reduce
to
and
continue
baking
for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Combine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cut and serve with cream of mushroom soup (no milk added) and top with slivered almonds, if desired.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in syrup.
Beat in flour and salt.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, eggs (alternate eggs, one at a time, with flour) and vanilla.
Stir in sour cream last.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add salt and flavoring.
Dilute milk with water and add to mixture.
Serve it sprinkled with ground nutmeg.
Fix a day ahead of time or at least 24 hours.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook pork roast in crock-pot until done.
Take out of pot, cut up, pour broth from roast away.
Mix mustard, celery seed, cloves, brown sugar, vinegar, onion and ketchup together in a saucepan. Simmer 20 minutes.
Take cut up roast, put back in crock-pot. Pour sauce over meat.
Cook 2 to 3 hours in crock-pot.

title: sour cream coffeecake
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla, mixing well.
Blend in flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix until smooth.
Spoon half the batter in well-greased and floured 9-inch angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of the sugar mixture on top of the batter.
Sprinkle half the nuts on top of the sugar.
Spoon in remaining batter.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture and nuts on top.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Top may be sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cook bacon in large frying pan until crisp, add meat browning on medium heat. Transfer meat to covered casserole dish, sprinkle with flour and set aside.

title: best ever fruit cake
directions: Before you start, sample the whiskey to check for quality. Good isn't it?
Now go ahead.
Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the whiskey again as it must be just right.
To be sure the whiskey is of the highest quality, pour one level cup into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat. With an electric mixer, beat butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon thugar and beat again.

title: iced cookies(from the turpin family - shared by mary erle turpin)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream; add vanilla.
Roll in a ball.
Cover with waxed paper.
Chill at least 1 hour.
(May put in freezer for a very short time.)
Roll about 1/2-inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Bake about 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: golden coconut balls
directions: Spread coconut in a large shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes until golden brown. Turn into a small pie pan and cool. Roll ice cream scoops in the coconut to cover all sides.
Place in pan. Cover and freeze until ready to serve.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran and let stand. Mix sugar with shortening. Beat in eggs and buttermilk. Add wet bran. Combine flour, most of Bran Flakes, soda and salt. Stir into above ingredients. Mixture thickens as it stands. Bake however many muffins you want. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Store rest of the batter in covered container. Allow room for expansion. Will keep for 6 weeks.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill. The jello is used dry. You can change flavors and fruits as you want. Serves 8 to 10.

title: big hotcakes
directions: Mix ingredients, heat large skillet, melt a little butter in pan.
Pour a thin layer of batter in pan, cook, flip, cook other side.
Serve rolled with jelly and sour cream, or rolled with syrup and powdered sugar and sausage.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a small pan; boil for 1 minute. Cool completely. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and toss lightly. Pour marinade over vegetable mixture and stir gently. Cover salad and refrigerate overnight.

title: french roast chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 5 ingredients in a food processor or blender.
Insert under skin of chicken quarters. Combine melted butter, lemon juice and 3 tablespoons mustard.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the sugar, oil and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Sift flour with soda and salt and stir into the sugar mixture.
Add apples and nuts and beat well.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Better if made three days ahead of time.

title: beef soup(makes about 13 quarts)
directions: Use 18 quart kettle to mix in.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cook about 15 minutes at 375°, stirring often.
When pudding begins to thicken, turn oven back to 300° and cook until solid.
(Total baking time approximately 45 minutes.)

title: light tempura batter
directions: In bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Add water and egg.
Stir until smooth.
May add basil or dill.
Use for shrimp, chicken and all kinds of vegetables.
Heat oil to 375°.

title: pork goulash - gulasz wieprzowy
directions: Cut meat into large cubes, well trimmed.
Put meat, onions and seasonings in heavy casserole and simmer, tightly covered, turning occasionally until meat browns.
Dust with flour.
Add soup stock, tomato puree and the parboiled potatoes.
Cover and continue to simmer until meat and potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: G
rind green tomatoes before measuring.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 45 minutes, until almost all moisture is evaporated.
Pack in hot jars and seal until ready to use.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle a yellow cake mix over filling.
Melt 3/4 cup butter and sprinkle over cake mix. Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with a generous amount of nuts.
Cook another 30 minutes.

title: cheese-zucchini sandwich
directions: For each serving, top toast with cheese slice, zucchini and onion.
Sprinkle with oregano, shredded cheese and bacon.
Cook, uncovered, on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and make cocktail size meatballs. Brown and drop in sauce to simmer until done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in a plastic bag.
Toss biscuit pieces in bag until well coated.
Layer biscuit pieces in well-greased Bundt pan, sprinkling nuts between layers. Melt brown sugar and margarine together.
Pour over contents of pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: beef with buckwheat noodles in spicy peanut sauce
directions: Cut steak across grain on diagonal into thin strips.
In a wok, heat oil over hig heat until hot, swirling to coat sides of pan.
Add steak and stir-fry until meat loses its red color, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove to plate.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Add vanilla, fruits and nuts. Drop on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, green pepper, onion, egg, Worcestershire sauce, saltine crackers, salt, pepper, tomato juice and 3/4 cup catsup in bowl; mix well.
