Spoon into microwave-safe dish. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until cooked through, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Top with remaining catsup. Microwave for 1 minute longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Break up lettuce in a large bowl.
Brown hamburger; drain and cool on paper towel.
Add cheese and hamburger to lettuce.
Cut up tomatoes.
Crunch Doritos in bag and mix together Miracle Whip and taco sauce.
Add the last three things just before serving.

title: spicy mexican rice
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil; put on medium heat.
Add rice and onions; saute about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes, or until tender.
Yields 5 servings.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Boil 5 minutes over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add one 12 ounce package of chocolate chips.
Stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes and onion on a large piece of heavy-duty foil (about 20 x 20-inches); dot with butter.
Combine the cheese, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; sprinkle over potatoes.
Fold foil up around potatoes and add broth.
Seal the edges of foil well.
Grill, covered, over medium coals, for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: tiny ham-filled tomatoes
directions: Thinly slice tops from tomatoes; remove pulp and drain shells upside down on paper towels.
In small bowl with fork, combine deviled ham, sour cream and horseradish.
Fill tomatoes. Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 20 appetizers.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with the cracker crumbs and press into a 9 x 13-inch oblong
pan.
Melt remaining 2 sticks of butter and beat with eggs and powdered sugar for 15 minutes and spread over the crumb mixture.
Spread the drained pineapple over the sugar mixture.
Next, cut up the bananas on top of the pineapple and cover all with Cool Whip.
Cover with foil and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Orange Icing.

title: my favorite snack:  pizza bagels
directions: Put sauce on a bagel. Put cheese on the sauce.
Put it in the oven and bake it!

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in remaining flour 1 cup at a time, to make a stiff dough.
Spoon batter into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal also.
Cover with a damp cloth; let rise in a warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.
To serve, slice and toast.
Makes about 16 slices per loaf.

title: herb-seasoned popcorn
directions: Prepare popcorn, one package at a time, according to directions.
Carefully open each bag and add 1/2 teaspoon of each herb.
Close bag and shake.
Pour into containers.
Add nuts and toss gently.
Yields 9 quarts.

title: amarillo barbecue sauce
directions: Heat and blend until smooth.
Baste meat on grill.

title: dannon vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: cranberry salsa
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor and chop until blended. Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight. This is good "appetizer".

title: norwegian crowns
directions: Put yolks through strainer into creamed butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and continue to cream.
Add flour and almonds; blend well.
Force dough through cookie press or roll out on floured board and use cookie cutter.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Watch cookies; they burn easily!

title: catsup salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.

title: six layer toffee torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) round cake pans.
In large bowl, measure first 9 ingredients.
With mixer on low, beat until blended, constantly scraping bowl.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons instant coffee in 1 cup boiling water.
Add to bowl. Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Spoon batter into pans evenly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted into middle comes out clean.
Invert onto wire rack to cool completely.

title: grandma's molasses drop cookies
directions: Boil lard or shortening and molasses.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Add flour to make a stiff dough, little stiffer than cake and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crispy chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and pepper in a large plastic bag.
Stir chicken into eggs;
Remove chicken with slotted spoon and place in bag with baking mix. Shake bag until chicken is coated; remove chicken from bag.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Stir-fry carrots 2 minutes; add green pepper and stir-fry 2 minutes. Remove from skillet.
Keep warm. Add remaining oil to skillet.
Heat until hot.
Stir-fry chicken until golden brown. Add carrots, green pepper and onion. Stir-fry until warm, about 2 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken breast until done and take off the bone.
In a separate bowl mix tomatoes, soups and cheese together and place in microwave until cheese has melted.
Add chicken to the cheese mixture.
Crumble up Doritos and place in bottom of pan.
Layer chicken mixture and Doritos.
Cook at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Crumble corn flakes on top and pour melted butter over flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Take spoonful and make into ball.
Press with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 54 cookies.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Trim the crust from the bread.
Place 6 slices on the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer on top 1/2 of the ham and cheese.
Cover with the remaining 6 slices of bread and repeat the ham and cheese layer.
Combine the eggs, milk and mustard. Pour over the layers in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Slice in squares and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: original green bean casserole
directions: Two 9 ounce packages frozen cut green beans (cooked and drained) may be used in place of the canned green beans.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes and drain.
Cook rice (not Minute rice).
Saute onion in margarine until tender, but not brown. Combine broccoli, rice and onion.
Dilute soup with milk and pour over broccoli and rice mixture.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese last 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place chicken, bell pepper, carrots and onion in bowl with Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce; set aside.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to direction on package.
Set aside.
Place butter in skillet and add chicken mixture.
Cook until done; add Rice-A-Roni mix and serve.
Serves 6.

title: smothered beef with carrots
directions: Prepare sauce by combining 2/3 cup ketchup, 1 Tbsp. honey, 2 tsp. lemon juice and a dash of hot pepper sauce;
set aside. Grill or broil 2 to 2 1/2 pounds broiler-fryer pieces, brushing with sauce during the last 5 to 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: angel whispers
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually.
Add remaining ingredients (except glaze) and chill.
Measure level teaspoonful of dough for cookies on ungreased baking sheet and flatten.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: creamy squash casserolemidland, texas
directions: Boil squash until tender for 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain well.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Combine potatoes, egg, onion and parsley.
Shape into round cakes, about 3/4-inches thick.
Roll in flour.
Bake cakes on both sides until brown in hot Crisco.
Very good.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour and spices.
Mix in large bowl sugar and oil. Continue mixing and add molasses, eggs and flour mixture.
Add 2 teaspoons baking soda, mixed in 1/8 cup hot water.
Beat lightly and quickly.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: chicken tacos
directions: In a 9 or 10-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add onion and garlic and saute until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken and cook until heated through. Divide chicken mixture into taco shells, then top with cheese and lettuce.

title: golden potato puff
directions: Coat an 8-cup tube mold well with margarine.
Sprinkle with corn meal, tap out excess.
Cook potatoes in lightly-salted water until tender; drain well.
Shake pan over low heat to dry and fluff potatoes; mash.
Beat egg whites until they stand in firm peaks. Separately beat egg yolks until thick.

title: oatmeal scotties
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract (or orange rind) until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch flavored morsels.
Drop by measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crisp cookies.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating it into whites.
Add nuts, dates and chips, stirring in gently.
Grease cookie sheets and drop batter by teaspoonfuls.
Place in 350° oven and turn heat off as you put them in.
Leave in oven at least two hours or overnight.
In other words, "Forget them."

title: lattice-top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, veggies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spread mixture into a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, combine biscuit mix, egg and milk to form a soft dough. Spoon over hot chicken mixture to form a lattice design.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden.
Top lattice with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts and onions are slightly browned.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except hard-cooked eggs.
Pack half the meat mixture into a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Arrange shelled hard-cooked eggs in a lengthwise row through center of loaf.
Pack remaining meat mixture over eggs.
Bake in 350° oven until done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Grease an angel food cake pan and place chopped nuts on bottom. Melt together margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle half over nuts.
Place a layer of frozen rolls (12 to 16) on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 pkg. butterscotch pudding over rolls, then pour over remainder melted sugar mixture.
Cover and let stand overnight.
In the morning, heat oven to 350° and bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly and invert pan on serving plate.

title: homemade clay
directions: Mix together flour, salt and alum.
Add water and stir.
For different colors, you may add food coloring.
It's ready for play.

title: sweet and sour tuna
directions: Start by draining water from can of tuna.
In large bowl, mix tuna with the rest of the ingredients.
May be served cool, chilled or warm over bed of rice or pilaf.

title: pyrophy(perogie)
directions: Combine water, egg and salt and add to 3 cups flour.
Mix well; add and knead in the fourth cup of flour until smooth and elastic. Brush with oil and set aside for 15 minutes.
Roll out as for pie crust and cut with a round cookie cutter.
Place the round on the palm of your hand.
Place a spoonful of the filling (recipe follows) on it; fold over to make a half circle.
Press the edges together with your fingers, making sure the edges are free of filling.
Have the edges sealed well to prevent the filling from running out.
Place the pyrophy on a tea towel, side by side, without touching each other.
Cover with another tea towel to keep them from drying out.
Drop into salted boiling water and stir with a wooden spoon to keep them from sticking to the bottom of the pan; boil for 4 or 5 minutes.
Drain in a colander and pour 1 cup cold water over them.
Drain; place in a bowl sprinkled with oil and toss gently to coat evenly.
Chopped onion, browned in oil, could be used if desired.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Add hot and bell peppers to soak in 2 cups sugar for 20 minutes.
Put green tomatoes in enamel pan and pour the salt over them.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Next, pour off the brine.
Mix tomatoes and peppers together.
In large pot, put the sugar and vinegar and heat it.
Add the peppers and tomatoes.
Let simmer, slowly, until tender or changes color.
Do not boil.
Seal in jars. Makes approximately 8 quarts.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients in a small bowl, mix dry yeast with 1 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add to dry ingredients along with the egg.
If dry, add a little more warm water.
Makes 3 round or 2 long pizzas.

title: cheesy lemon bars
directions: Combine cake mix, egg and butter until moistened.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan, buttered on bottom only.
Blend frosting mix and cheese.
Reserve 1/3 cup of cheese mixture.
Add 2 eggs to remaining frosting mix; heat 3 to 5 minutes and spread over cake. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; let cool and spread with remaining frosting mixture.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Prepare vegetables; mix with seasonings, sugar and vinegar. Boil 20 minutes and seal in cans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
When soft, mix cream cheese, Kraft cheese, the pimentos, dried onions and the garlic.
Mix well. Roll into a ball.
Roll the cheese ball in the pecans until covered.

title: hot and spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven over low heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Good!

title: coconut bon balls
directions: Mix in a large bowl and shape into balls.
You may use less or more coconut depending on consistency.
You should be able to place a toothpick into the balls to pick them up to dip in coating.
Lay bon balls on wax paper.

title: golfer's beef stew
directions: Place meat in large casserole.
Combine soups and wine.
Pour over beef.
Cover and bake in 250° oven three hours.

title: old-timey fruitcake
directions: Chop fruit and nuts. Roll in flour. Add all ingredients together and mix. Press in a pan and bake in a slow 275° oven until done.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add chocolate and salt.
Add water. Cook in heavy saucepan until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Spread on cake while hot.

title: wisconsin chili soup
directions: In a large soup/stock pot brown ground beef and drain fat; set aside.
Saute onions and celery. Add beef and stir.
Add all other ingredients except macaroni.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
During last 1/2 hour add macaroni; stir occasionally.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar and butter together. Press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: impossible cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients, except pie filling and Streusel, until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Spoon pie filling evenly over top.
Bake 25 minutes. Sprinkle with Streusel.
Bake until Streusel is brown, about 10 minutes longer.

title: sam's easy bake apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix apples and spices.
Spread in greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/12).
Beat remaining 5 ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.

title: breakfast tortillas
directions: Scramble egg substitute adding Bac*Os when eggs are half cooked.
Put tortillas in steamer for 2 to 3 minutes.
After eggs are cooked, place an ample amount on one side of tortilla and roll tightly.
These may be frozen and reheated in microwave.

title: debbie nicholson's excellent moist zucchini bread
directions: Blend all dry ingredients. Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Add chopped nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cook the potatoes until tender. Mash and add ingredients.
Add milk slowly and whip the potatoes until fluffy. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish; do not cover. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Refrigerate drinks overnight.
Put sherbet in punch bowl. Pour drinks over sherbet.
Use lime or orange, depending on color needed.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain.
Chill in cold water for 1 hour. Add all ingredients and toss.
Chill in fridge for awhile before serving.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in a mixer.
Add egg and beat.
Add carrots and lemon extract; blend together.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet; flatten.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Frost with thin icing made from powdered sugar mixed with juice and grated peel from 1/2 orange.

title: plum pie
directions: Cream butter into flour.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Spread dough with hands in bottom of jelly roll pan and up sides.
Arrange plums in rows on top of dough.
Mix 4 beaten eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar and pour over plums.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt margarine; add crumbs.
Mix well.
Add sugar, pecans, peanut butter and vanilla.
Make into balls.
Melt wax in double boiler.
Add chocolate and mix well.
Drop balls into chocolate. Place on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Repeat process.

title: peanut butter and jelly french toast
directions: Spread peanut butter on 6 slices of bread.
Spread jelly on other 6 slices.
Put 1 slice of each together to form sandwiches.

title: party cheese ring
directions: Mix
chopped pecans, mayo, cheese, onions and hot sauce together
and
form
a
ring
on plate.
Put strawberry jam in center of ring prior to serving.
Serve Party Cheese Ring with crackers.

title: cheese log
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except nuts. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed until well blended.
Can stir in 1/4 cup of nuts, but I just put nuts on outside.
Cover.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Spread nuts on waxed paper or foil.
Form chilled mixture into log shape.
Roll in nuts until all nuts are rolled in.
Wrap in some foil and chill.
Can be frozen and thaws quite fast.

title: zucchini jack casserole
directions: Slice zucchini crosswise, 1/4 inch thick (about 7 cups).
In large bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt, baking powder and flour until smooth.
Stir in parsley, garlic, onion, green chiles, cheese and zucchini.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss croutons in the melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, until set in center and squash is tender.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Spread butter over the bottom of a heavy, large baking pan with 1-inch high sides.
Arrange bread slices in pan.

title: squash and carrot casserole
directions: Combine onion, carrots and squash in saucepan.
Cook with salted water until tender. Drain off liquid and mash vegetables. This is one layer.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing (second layer).
Mix sour cream and soup (third layer).
Layer these, starting and ending with the stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Fits in 3-quart container.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water, pineapple, grated cheese, sugar and salt.
Chill until slightly congealed. Fold in whipped cream and chill until set.

title: oven barbecue chicken wings
directions: Mix barbecue sauce, lemon juice and mustard together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle the cheese on top. Mix all other ingredients well and pour over bread and cheese. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: frosty pate
directions: Bring the liver sausage and cream cheese to room temperature. Mash together with a fork.
Add the onion, parsley, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into a ball and place in a waxed paper lined bowl; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Whip together the 3 ounces cream cheese (at room temperature) and the sour cream. Frost the pate.
Serve with crackers.

title: layered vegetable-herb salad
directions: Be sure all vegetables are dry to prevent salad from getting watery.
In 9 x 13 inch baking dish, place lettuce in an even layer.
Distribute items next 6 ingredients in even layers over lettuce Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, Italian seasoning, garlic salt and pepper.
Spread a layer of dressing over top of salad; serve remaining dressing on side.
Cover salad with plastic wrap.
Place another 9 x 13 pan on top of salad and weight with heavy cans or use clean bricks wrapped in plastic wrap to press down salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: red bean soup
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.

title: ice chocolate
directions: Cook in a double boiler.
Sweeten to taste and flavor with vanilla.
Cool and serve in tall glasses filled with ice. Decorate with whipped cream.

title: ban-apple crisp
directions: Slice the apples and bananas into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with juice of 1/2 lemon and 1/4 cup sugar. Make crumb topping by blending the butter, brown sugar, graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (325° for glass pan).

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Press into a container or mold sprayed with nonstick spray.
Chill.
Unmold on tray or plate.
Top with parsley.
Serve with small bread sticks or crackers.

title: quickie fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa together in glass mixing bowl. Pour milk in bowl and then place the butter on top of the powdered sugar and cocoa (DO NOT MIX). Put in microwave until the butter has melted, about 3 to 4 minutes or longer depending on the microwave power level. Remove; stir, then quickly add vanilla. Stir in. Then add nuts, if desired. Pour into plastic cake size pan. Spread out and then refrigerate for 1 hour OR 20 minutes in the freezer. Take, cut and ENJOY.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in any size baking cups.

title: ethel's cream gravy
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir together making a thick paste.
Cook until smooth.
Add milk and stock, stirring constantly until desired thickness is reached.
Bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple cuchin
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and bake 10 minutes.
Put on the apples or peaches.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon.
Beat the sour cream and egg.
Pour on top. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: currant scones
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Cut in butter with pastry cutter until mixture resembles crumbs.
Stir in milk and mix until dough holds together.
Add currants plumped in the brandy, sherry or orange juice.
Wrap in plastic and chill well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured board roll out dough 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch thick (1/2-inch for tiny scones, 3/4-inch for 2 1/2-inch rounds). Place close together on lightly buttered baking sheet.
Brush tops with milk, and bake in hot oven until golden brown about 13 to 18 minutes.
Serve warm with butter and/or strawberry jam.
(For an English tea, split open, spread with strawberry jam, then place a generous spoonful of whipped cream on the top.)
Yummy!!!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour, jello, sugar and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Let cool. Slice strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Cover with Dream Whip.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix 1/2 cup pecans in the cheese, then mix all other ingredients in cheese.
Mix well and shape into 2 balls.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: pineapple snow
directions: In a medium bowl, dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water. Add cold water, drain juice from pineapple and add.
Chill until slightly thickened, add egg white.
Place bowl of gelatin mixture in a bowl of ice and water and beat until fluffy thick and double in volume.
Fold in drained pineapple.
Turn into individual dessert dishes and chill until firm.

title: no mix bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle 1 package butterscotch chips in the pan.
Sprinkle the Angel Flake coconut in pan.
Add 1 package of chocolate chips and the chopped nutmeats.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over the ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and butter or margarine; press on bottom of oblong cake pan.
Save a few crumbs for topping.

title: six-week muffins
directions: Mix boiling water and baking soda; allow to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Mix with water and soda; then add remaining ingredients and mix in a large bowl.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Spoon into muffin cups or tins without stirring.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: pa's apple stack cake
directions: Spread apple butter onto graham crackers and stack up like they were in package.
Make three stacks and let set for 2 to 2 1/2 hours before slicing them.
Place on cake plate and store in refrigerator.

title: holeless doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add butter, flour and beaten egg yolks.
Mix until smooth.
Let rise 3 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat.
(I use Fry Daddy.)
Fry until brown.
Put on paper towel to drain off fat.
Take cool doughnut; put in a bag with sugar and shake until coated.
Cinnamon can be added to sugar in shake bag for some of doughnuts.

title: fresh mustard greens
directions: Wash greens several times to remove all grit.
Put chops in large pot sprayed with nonstick spray and brown lightly on both sides.
Gradually add the greens and stir occasionally until all the greens are in the pot.
Cover and cook until greens are tender, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; add one cup boiling water.
Stir well. Bake slow in large pan at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in greased large baking dish. Mix cans of soup with water. Pour over rice and chicken. Salt to taste. Sprinkle onion soup over top of all and cover tightly. Cook 2 hours at 350°. Reduce to 325° the last hour if it is browning too fast.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 quart.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all together and add mayonnaise.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, egg, vanilla, banana, flour and cinnamon. Mix until well blended. Stir in oats and pecans. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing cookies about 2 inches apart. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown. Remove from pan immediately and cool on rack. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Start by sauteing celery, onion and garlic in 1/2 stick margarine, then chicken broth, creamed soup, milk, broccoli and carrot.
Cook about 20 minutes, then add seasoning and cheese, cook 10 minutes more.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes whole in skins until pricked with fork are done and not soft.
Peel while hot and cut in halves.
When cold, cut in cubes; add bell pepper (cut up), celery (stripped of strings) and eggs.
Add pickle relish and a touch of salad seasoning, oregano and mayonnaise, not Miracle Whip.

title: roasted leg of lamb with garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place lamb on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Rub with lemon juice.
Mash garlic and rosemary together. Make little slits outside of lamb and stuff with garlic and rosemary mixture.
Sprinkle lamb with paprika.
Roast at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°; insert meat thermometer and continue cooking until thermometer registers 10° below desired doneness (about 1 hour and 50 minutes). Remove from oven; let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with mint jelly, mint sauce or Port wine sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: flag cake
directions: Slice 1 cup of the strawberries; set aside.
Halve remaining strawberries; set aside.
Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices.
Top with 1 cup of sliced strawberries, 1 cup of blueberries and all of the Cool Whip.
Place strawberry halves and remaining 1/3 cup of blueberries on Cool Whip to create a flag design.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: cheesy and easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coat a 9 x 13 baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Spread about 1 1/2 cups of sauce over the bottom. Place 3 lasagna noodles lengthwise over the sauce. (Don't worry if the uncooked lasagna noodles don't extend the full length of your baking pan; they will expand in baking.) Top with another 1 1/2 cups of sauce, then scatter the spinach over the sauce. Drizzle with olive oil. Top with spinach with half of the Ricotta cheese, placing it randomly in heaping tablespoonfuls. Arrange half of the Mozzarella slices on top and sprinkle with half of the grated dry Jack cheese. Top with 3 more lengthwise lasagna noodles, another 1 1/2 cups of sauce and then the remaining Ricotta and Mozzarella. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until bubbling and the top is browned. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes at room temperature, then cut in squares to serve. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale and chill.
Add ginger ale immediately before serving.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease a 12-cup muffin pan. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a medium bowl; make a well in the center. Mix milk, egg, oil, banana and walnuts in a small bowl. Pour mixture into well. Mix batter just until moistened; do not overmix. Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups. Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean or until muffins are golden brown, about 15 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: mom's buttermilk pralines
directions: Cook sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt in large heavy saucepan until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and cool. Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until stiff and creamy. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cape cod chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and powder in plastic bag.
Toss the chicken to coat evenly.
Melt butter in pan; brown chicken pieces. Combine
remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over chicken pieces, cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes until tender.

title: festive cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple with juice.
Mix well.
Put in individual molds or 9 x 9-inch dish.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp with orzo and broccoli
directions: In large skillet, bring broth, tomatoes and broccoli to a boil over high heat.
Add orzo; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raw, cleaned shrimp, salt and pepper.
Return to a simmer; cover.
Stirring occasionally, cook 3 to 4 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink and broccoli and orzo are tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Feta and basil. Serves 4.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Melt margarine in oblong Pyrex baking dish.
Mix the flour, brown sugar and pecans into the melted margarine.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool well.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla and pour into cooled crust.
Add pie filling on top. If desired, top with small carton of Cool Whip.

title: grandmama harris' broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sharp cheese.
Mix 2 cups bread crumbs in 3/4 stick melted margarine; stir until coated.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made the day before serving. Remove from refrigerator about 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and cut into small pieces chicken, saving 1 cup of broth. Mix together all ingredients except 3/4 cup of stuffing mix. Spray casserole dish and add ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mushroom tofu quiche
directions: Combine tofu, egg whites, whole egg, milk, oregano, garlic powder, 1/2 cup cheese, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/8 teaspoon salt in blender.
Cover and blend or process until smooth.
Stir in corn and dried onion.
Prepare a 9-inch pie plate by spreading margarine over the bottom and sides and sprinkling with bread crumbs.
Pour tofu mixture into pie plate.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (a knife inserted near the center should come out clean). Arrange tomato wedges on top of quiche and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted (about 3 minutes).
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: butter roll
directions: Open buns and turn brown side up.
Melt butter in small container and pour over buns.
Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour over buns.
Bake for 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: strawberry chiffon
directions: In a small pan, add water, sugar and gelatin.
Cook over low heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Stir occasionally and remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries and chill for 1/2 hour. When mixture is cold, stir in yogurt until completely combined. Gently fold in egg whites.
Store in refrigerator about 4 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip and condensed milk; stir until smooth. Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges; add to mixture.
Mix in nuts to taste.
Pour in graham cracker shells and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: linda's homemade low-fat granola
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
Combine honey and oil and stir into the oats.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from the oven.

title: 1 2 3 4 cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder 2 or 3 times.
Cream sugar and butter until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add milk and flour a little at a time until smooth.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: best brownies
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Gradually add sugar and beat until thick. Melt butter and cocoa together; mix into sugar mixture.
Mix in flour.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sue's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and add bacon to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add the sherbet.
Stir until all sherbet is melted.
Beat the Dream Whip with the milk and vanilla.
Combine the 2 mixtures and add the oranges, saving a few slices to decorate the top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare
pudding according to package directions, using 3 cups skim milk.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Reserve 6 Nilla wafers and 1 banana.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Add enough evaporated milk to make paste.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add rest of milk and finish filling pan with sweet milk.
Cook in a double boiler until it begins to thicken.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage and drain off fat.
In a mixing bowl beat eggs and add milk.
Add cubed bread, salt and mustard.
Add cheese and sausage.
Pour into glass dish (8 x 13-inch) and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Set out and cut.

title: the best doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients and fry in deep oil until golden brown.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Combine flour mixture with shortening mixture.
Stir in candy pieces.
Shape into rolls and chill overnight or several hours.
Cut into thin slices and bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni	according to package directions.
Brown hamburger with
onion
and	add
sauce
and soup and mix well. Place in
casserole
dish.	Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chinese beef and broccoli
directions: Heat wok or skillet on high.
Add oil; when hot, add salt, garlic and ginger.
Remove before they burn.
Add beef; cook until tender.
Add broccoli and cook about 2 minutes, until crisp.
Add sherry, soy sauce and chicken stock.
Add cornstarch in water. Stir-fry 10 to 30 seconds until slightly thickened and glossy. Serve over rice.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add and mix after alternately adding flour to creamed mixture with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and flour. Set aside. Combine melted oleo, eggs and vanilla into flour mixture until just moistened. Grease muffin tins. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool before taking out of pan.

title: beef roast
directions: Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Add ingredients and cook together 4 hours at 300°.
Delicious.

title: pork fried rice
directions: In a large skillet or wok, fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook until onion starts to soften.
Push onion and bacon aside and scramble eggs in the center.
Mix bacon, onion and eggs together, then push to side.
In center of skillet, mix ginger, celery seed, garlic and soy sauce.
Stir in bacon mixture.
Add rice.
Stir until thoroughly mixed and all rice is coated.
More soy sauce can be added if necessary.
Cook until rice is thoroughly heated.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Rinse berries and shake off water.
Peel, slice and core apples.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine fruit and put into pan.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in oleo.
Sprinkle crumbs onto fruit.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep casserole.
Let cool.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and water.
Pour batter on top of butter.
Do not stir.
Pour sweetened fruit on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: beef porcupines in tomato gravy
directions: Combine ground	beef, rice, bread crumbs, salt, parsley and 2 tablespoons
water.
Shape into an 8-inch square or pack evenly in an 8-inch
pan.
Cut 3 lines on one side and 4 lines on the other side
to
make
20	equal
sections.
Shape each section into a meatball.
Heat
oil in a large skillet. Brown meatballs in hot oil over medium heat, turning frequently.

title: yummy pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first four ingredients together until smooth.
Toss flour and chips together and add to cheese mixture. Pour into pie shell and bake for 35 minutes, or until center is springy.
Cool before serving.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Fry hamburger in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.

title: pork and peach bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make stuffing mix according to package directions, decreasing water by 1/4 cup; stir in 1/4 cup preserves. Spoon stuffing into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Brown pork chops in oil over medium heat.
Arrange pork chops and peaches over stuffing.
Spoon remaining 1/4 cup preserves over chops.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pork chops are tender. Garnish with parsley.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add cheese last.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: macaroni casserole(overnight)
directions: Stir and put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook and put into refrigerator overnight or all day.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Pare
eggplant; cut in 1 inch squares.	Cook in boiling salted water
8 minutes.
Add egg, milk, butter, onion and dry bread crumbs.
Place
in	greased 1 quart buttered dish.	Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix zucchini and onion and add croutons, chicken, soup and sour cream.
Trim ends of zucchini and slice in halves lengthwise.
Boil in salted water until tender, about 4 minutes.
Use 1 1/2-quart casserole; use more croutons or bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: johnny cake
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients. Bake in a square baking pan in 350° oven. Serve hot and cut into squares.

title: reba's slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Good luck and bon appetit.

title: shaker beef goulash
directions: In plastic bag combine first four ingredients.
Shake.
In large skillet add 2 tablespoons of oil and brown shaken ingredients.
Add onions, 1 cup water and apple juice.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/4 hours until tender.
Add carrots, parsley and spices.
Simmer 30 minutes more.
Blend 1/2 cup water and 3 tablespoons of flour.
Stir into stew.
Cook and stir until bubbly.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat and onion.
In large casserole arrange alternate layers of meat mixture and vegetables, beginning and ending with meat.
Combine soup with water and pour over top.
Punch holes in mixture to allow soup to go through.
Cover and bake at 325° about 2 hours.
Melt cheese on top (optional).

title: apple pie
directions: Cut up apples as for regular pie.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Mix flour, remaining brown sugar and butter until crumbly.
Spread this mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and crust is golden, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: salisbury steak with onions and peppers
directions: Heat Crisco oil in large (at least 12-inch) skillet on medium heat.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Cook and stir until tender. Remove to serving platter.
Cover to keep warm.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese, with 1 cup boiling water; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir well; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: brown betty
directions: Put a layer of peeled and sliced apples in a baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and then bread crumbs. Repeat, ending with bread crumbs and butter on top. Sprinkle with water. Cook until apples are tender (about 30 to 40 minutes) and bread crumbs are brown in 400° oven.

title: claire's lemon pie
directions: Beat milk and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into shell. Chill thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter, milk and cream of chicken soup.
Mix broccoli, rice and soup mixture together.
Mix in Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Combine and boil water, shortening or oil, sugar, salt, cloves, cinnamon and raisins. Cool.

title: b.l.t. soup
directions: In Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and keep warm, but don't let get soggy.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon grease, trying to save all browned residue in pan.
Cook onion in bacon grease until translucent, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into balls; roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: goober salad
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Put peanuts in food processor and chop.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Serve with apple slices for a caramel apple taste. (Sprinkle apples with Fruit-Fresh to keep from turning dark as quick or dip in pineapple juice.)

title: 3 cheese spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to directions. Cool in cold water.
Set aside.
Saute red pepper and onion until tender in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Combine spinach, pepper, onion, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and egg; set aside.

title: ranch baked fish
directions: Melt butter in a 13X9-inch baking dish. Place fish filets on top of butter in dish. Mix dry ranch dressing, mayonnaise and milk. Pour over fish, top with sliced cheese. Crumble crushed chips over cheese. Bake in 350 oven for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sugar free cream pie
directions: Combine 1/2 package (5 1/2) crackers with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Press into pie plate and microwave for 2 minutes to set.

title: cottage cheese delight(lo-cal)
directions: I choose the fruit and gelatin in the same flavor such as strawberries and strawberry Jell-O, peaches and peach Jell-O, cherries and cherry Jell-O, etc.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix the sugar, vinegar, oil, tomato soup and Worcestershire sauce in a boiler and let boil 2 minutes.
Add carrots, onions and pepper.
Mix well and let marinate in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Mash potatoes in large bowl of electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat at high speed until smooth and creamy-light.
Stir in chopped chives.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with melted butter. Put in bottom of 9 x 13 dish (hold back 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping).

title: sesame citrus
directions: Combine grapefruit sections, orange sections and orange rind in bowl.
Chill in refrigerator.
Mix honey, yogurt and sesame seed in small bowl.
Chill.
Add dressing to fruit.
Mix gently. Spoon into serving dishes, then sprinkle with almonds.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix drained crushed pineapple, nuts, sugar, lemon juice and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip and put into 2 (9-inch) baked and cooled graham cracker crusts and refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: vodka punch
directions: Soak strawberries in vodka for 1 hour.
Add orange juice and cranberry juice.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet. Make a block of ice to float in punch.

title: death by chocolate(this is a chocolate lover's delight!)
directions: Bake brownies according to package.
Let cool!
Prepare chocolate mousse according to package.
Break candy into small pieces.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; garnish with ice ring and fruit slices. Serves 40 to 60 cups.

title: chicken casserole(microwave)
directions: Cook and cube chicken breasts.
Set aside.
Mix together celery, water chestnuts and onions.
Set aside.
Make sauce of mayonnaise, soup and curry powder.
Melt butter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and butter melts.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt to mixture, stirring well.
Pour into pastry shell and top with pecan halves. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: strawberry mold dessert
directions: Mix the 2 packages jello with 1 cup hot water until thoroughly dissolved.
Next add the cold water.
Put into fridge until it's just barely beginning to gel.
Remove from fridge and add the strawberries and whipped whipping cream.
Cut the cake into large bite sized pieces.
Add to other mixture.
Mix well.
Fold into an angel food cake pan and place in fridge overnight!

title: tuna time saver
directions: Break tuna into small pieces.
Stir in onion, pimento, rice and Tabasco sauce.
Pack into baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup with water and pour over tuna.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Combine milk and oil in cup; do not stir.
Add flour mixture all at once.
Mix with fork.
Shape into ball; divide into 2 portions.

title: mom's great omelets
directions: In pan, melt butter or margarine. Mix egg and water (whip). Pour into melted butter. Wait a few minutes until omelet starts getting solid around edges. Lift around edges so liquid from omelet can get to bottom of pan. Pour sour cream, parsley, pepper and onions into omelet. (Don't turn over yet.) Let simmer for about 2 minutes. Lift around edges only with spatula; take pan in hand and as you start to pour omelet, fold over using the pan.

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat potatoes well. Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: tarheel pie
directions: Put warm butter over chocolate chips and stir.
Blend all remaining ingredients and stir in chocolate chip mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: *Use London broil, top round or sirloin.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and incorporate evenly. In a small pot, heat water. Fill mug 1/3 full of cocoa mixture. Pour in hot water. Stir to combine. Also works with warm milk.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Pre heat oven to 425 degrees and coat muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray. Place dry ingredients in mixing bowl and blend with fork. Beat liquid ingredients together in separate bowl. Add liquid

& dry ingredients together and blend with a fork until flour is moistened and raisins and nuts. Fill muffin time 3/4 full place in oven and lower temperature to 400 degrees. Bake for 17-20 minutes or until browned

title: peanutty chocolate snack squares
directions: Line bottom of 8-inch square pan with graham cracker squares, cutting to fit as necessary.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in 2-quart microwave-proof bowl.
Microwave at High stirring every 2 minutes, until mixture boils; boil 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips, peanut butter and peanuts.
Pour over crackers; spread carefully.
Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: meat balls
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Mix rice, sausage, ground beef, onion, bell pepper, sage and salt and pepper.
Make in balls size of walnuts.
Drop into rapidly boiling water (enough to cover). When almost done, add 1 can tomatoes.
Cook few minutes longer. Serve immediately.

title: snowy mashed potatoes(serves 10)
directions: Mash potatoes; add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper. Beat at high speed until smooth.
Stir in chopped chives.
Spoon into lightly buttered 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place rice in shallow baking dish.
Drain vegetables.
Save liquid.
Spread vegetables over rice.
Mix reserved liquid with water to make 1 1/2 cups and mix with soup.
Pour over vegetables. Place chops on top and brush with soy sauce.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.
Sprinkle on onion rings and bake 10 minutes more.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli, chop onion, crumble bacon and mix together; add cheese.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and red wine vinegar, then pour over salad and stir well.
Refrigerate and serve.
This is good with big meals or hamburgers.

title: tiger bark candy
directions: Melt bark and peanut butter together in microwave 90 seconds. Spread on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave and swirl on top of bark and peanut butter mixture.
Cut or break when cool.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Combine.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.
May use green ice cubes for Christmas.

title: uncooked tomato relish
directions: Mix chopped tomatoes, onions, peppers, celery seed, and mustard seed.
Add salt.
Pour mixture into cheesecloth or colander, let drain overnight.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.
Will keep approximately 4 weeks, but it never lasts that long.
Enjoy.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crumble enough cookies in bottom of Pyrex dish to cover the bottom.
In a bowl, mix jello with 2 cups hot water and stir to dissolve.
Add ice cream and strawberry jello and stir until ice cream is melted.
Pour over cookies and chill until firm.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: roquefort potato casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until almost tender. Do not overcook. Allow to cool; slice lengthwise into very thin pieces.

title: luncheon meat baked bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, brown sugar and prepared mustard.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Separate onion slices into rings. Stir in the beans. Cut luncheon meat into 6 slices.
Spread with additional mustard.
Arrange on top of beans; sprinkle with additional brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: almond fruited cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients with 1/2 cup of the crushed cereal. Mix and refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Form into a ball.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: *Or substitute 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup light Karo for the white sugar and dark Karo.

title: strawberry breakfast bread
directions: Beat eggs with mixer until fluffy.
Add oil and mix.
Add sugar and berries and mix.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and baking soda into a large bowl.
Add to berry mix.
Add almonds. Bake 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut chicken wings apart.
Discard wing tips.
Sprinkle with Tony Chachere's to taste.
(If you want them hot add more seasoning to them.)
Let sit until you can see sweat droplets on the chicken. Drop into hot vegetable oil.
Cook until done (it doesn't take long to cook).
Take them out of the oil and drop them straight into the bar-b-que sauce of your choice.
Coat them heavily with sauce and put on a platter.
Do this until they are all done.
Let sit a few minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until sugar dissolves, about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in whipping cream.
Return to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Serve over ice cream, apple pie, etc.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In a medium bowl, stir together dry ingredients and spices; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar, egg, pumpkin and oil.
Add dry mixture to pumpkin mixture, stir just until moistened.
Fold in berries and almonds. Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans, cool completely. Wrap and store overnight.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Add beans and corn. Turn into 2-quart greased casserole dish and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and bisquick dumplings
directions: Add broth, basil, oregano. garlic and chicken to crockpot. Cook on low for 8-10 hours, or high 3-5
hours.
When it is almost done; mix cornstarch and water and place in a container with a lid; shake vigorously then stir mixture into crockpot broth to thicken.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, egg and juice from canned pineapple.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (4 to 5 minutes).
Cool.
Stir in whipped topping.
In a large bowl, mix apples, pineapple chunks, marshmallows and peanuts.
Pour in dressing mixture.
Toss well. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
In small saucepan, melt 1/2 cup butter with sugar, salt and evaporated milk.
Cool to lukewarm and stir into yeast mixture. Add sifted flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to coat all sides.
Cover and let rise unti doubled in bulk.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender at one time.
Blend until mixed together.
Pour mixture into 10-inch pie pan, slightly greased.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: california salad
directions: Mix and stir the first 4 ingredients until marshmallows are melted.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to set.
Stir in mayonnaise, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex bowl.
Return to refrigerator to congeal.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce.

title: hominy tamale casserole
directions: Fry onion, garlic and hominy until onion is clear and hominy starts to pop.
Add ground meat and warm.

Put in tamales, whipping as much juice off the papers into the pan as possible. Mix and cut up the tamales; cook until all are warmed through. Can be put in oven to bake for 20 minutes or just left to cook in frying pan.
Top with grated cheese and serve with a green or fruit salad, French bread and green vegetable.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix cucumber, onion and salt.
Drain after 1 hour.
Mix sugar, vinegar, black
pepper
and
turmeric.
Let
come
to a boil. Pour in cucumber mixture and let come to a second boil. Put in jars and seal tight. Real good to eat with brown beans.

title: road house cinnamon butter
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor and blend until mixture is smooth.
Serve with hot rolls or muffins.
Remainder may be stored in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg thoroughly.
Pat into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the powdered sugar, cream cheese and egg until well blended.
Pour on top of chocolate mixture. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares when cool.
The white portion will be very soft when baked, but will "set up" when cooled.

title: easy sausage casserole
directions: Combine sausage, onion and green pepper in a skillet; cook over medium heat until sausage is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine water, soup and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 minutes.
Add sausage mixture.
Spoon into a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Cover; bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Slice bread lengthwise. Do not scoop out.
Mix ground round, onion soup, Italian seasoning and tomato soup.
Spread evenly on both pieces of bread.
Put in oven at hottest temperature for approximately 20 minutes. Remove from oven and place sliced tomatoes on entire length of both pieces and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Place back in oven for 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese. Slice into serving size. Serves 4 to 6 hungry people.

title: pineapple cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients and cool.
Add marshmallows, cherries and pineapple.
Mix together.
Add whipped topping or whipping cream.
Can use leftover rice also.
Chill and serve.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fingers to make crust thinner.
Top each biscuit with teaspoon of pizza sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Cook according to directions on biscuit can.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Pour salsa over mixture.
Sprinkle onions and green pepper over salsa.
Top with cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients and knead for 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Place in refrigerator. Remove from refrigerator 2 hours before ready to bake.
Roll out into the shape desired and set aside for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Brush with margarine.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Remove crusts and slice bread into 1-inch cubes.
Melt cheese and butter in top of double boiler.
Stir vigorously after melted. Remove from heat and fold in egg whites.
Spear bread cubes with a 2 pronged fork or long wooden pick and dip mixture.
Shake gently to remove excess.
Chill overnight or freeze on cookie sheet.
Defrost if frozen for 30 minutes.
Put in 400° preheated oven.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 50.

title: vegetable calzones
directions: In small skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes.
Squeeze liquid from spinach, then chop.
In medium bowl combine onion mixture, spinach and cheese.
Cut dough crosswise into 6 equal pieces.
On lightly floured surface roll and fill.
Place calzones on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with enough mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla until well blended.
Add egg, flour, salt and baking soda to cream mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chewy macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and salt together.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time; blend well.
Beat in milk, butter, lemon juice and almond extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites and coconut into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in rim comes out clean.

title: cole slaw(that keeps)
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Set aside while preparing dressing.

title: cocoa biscuits
directions: Bring 1/2 cup sugar and water to a boil.
Add the rest of the sugar, flour and cocoa until as thick as you desire.
Serve over biscuits.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over powdered sugar in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: dill beans
directions: Wash and cook green beans until beans change color and are tender.
Pack beans upright in jar.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes in loaf pan.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots 1/4-inch thick or less.
Combine all ingredients in a stove top pan.
Cook on medium heat until tender. Boil off the remaining liquid and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom gray's macaroni and cheese
directions: Rub chicken halves with a little butter and herbs de Provence. Bake in 350° oven until tender, 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with potatoes and vegetable or rice cooked with spices.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt; set aside.
In a mixer bowl, beat sugar and shortening with electric mixer until light, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time, and the milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Put batter into a lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350` for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and congeal. Add topping.

title: pineapple coconut delight
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add pineapple, stir.
Add eggs, mix thoroughly. Add vanilla, mix. Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle with 1 c coconut.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 35 minutes.
For icing: mix butter,
milk, sugar, and vanilla. Bring to a boil. Sprinkle nuts on cake, spread hot icing over cake.

title: minestrone soup(no cholesterol; no fat)
directions: In 4-quart pot, combine juice, garlic, onion, zucchini, celery, carrots, bouillon and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Partially cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add oregano, basil, cabbage, tomatoes, kidney beans and garbanzo beans.
Continue cooking about 10 minutes.
Add pasta; cook until heated.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 servings.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with buttered bread, buttered side down.
Sprinkle cooked sausage on top.
Mix eggs and milk together well; pour on next.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken olivia
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees

title: layered beef and cheese supper
directions: Brown meat in oil;
drain.
Combine
green beans, 1 1/2 cups cheese, rice,
onion and celery; mix lightly.
Place meat in 11 3/4 x
1/2-inch	baking	dish.
Season
with salt and pepper. Top with rice mixture.

title: baked blueberry french toast
directions: Place bread into a jelly roll pan.
In a medium bowl, mix eggs, half-and-half and vanilla together, pour over bread, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, allspice and cornstarch together, fold in blueberries and place in a greased 13 X 9 baking pan.
Place chilled bread mixture on top of blueberry mixture; drizzle butter over bread.
Bake at 450 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: In a
1 1/2 quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in chicken, noodles, parsley and pimento.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir.
Top
with bread crumbs.
Bake for 5 or 10 minutes more.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar together.
Toss with raisins and bacon.

title: easy butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with soft margarine.
Save about 1/2 cup of the cookie crumbs.
Press cookies in a large 8 x 12-inch dish.

title: sour cream cheese sauce
directions: Cream all ingredients together and serve on hot baked potatoes.

title: zani honey cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, eggs, honey and vanilla.
Sift soda and salt with flour 2 times.
Mix all together.
Roll in small balls about 2 tablespoons of dough; flatten slightly on cookie sheet.
Do not crowd.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: baked mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream together flour and butter.
Beat remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab and lemon pepper bowtie salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
In large bowl, whisk together lemon juice, sour cream, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add cooked pasta, vegetables and Crab Delights.
Toss and serve.

title: creamed eggs 'n ham
directions: In frypan, melt butter on medium-low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Reduce heat to low; fold in cream cheese and stir until smooth.
Add eggs and ham.
Heat through.
Serve over muffins.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and lemon
juice
in
a 1 1/2 quart casserole.	Sprinkle with paprika. Bake
in
a 350° oven about 30 minutes until heated. (Celery and onion will be crunchy.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: toasted cheese puffs
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and onions.
Spread on individual Melba toasts.
Place under broiler or in toaster oven 3 to 5 minutes. Enjoy!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except oleo, milk and flour.
Put in casserole
dish.
Melt butter and mix flour and milk; pour over mixture.
Bake
for
30 to 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Process unpeeled orange in food processor until coarsely ground.
Combine with apples, drained pineapple and sugar in medium bowl; mix well.
Process cranberries in food processor until coarsely ground.
Add to orange mixture; mix well.
Chill, covered, for 8 hours.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: joanne's spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in baking pan; remove and cool.
Mix eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt well.
Add spinach, cheese and onion and mix well.
Put in pan and bake for 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Freezes well.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: chicken salad
directions: Let chicken and rice cool; add all in large mixing bowl and chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Do not beat egg whites.
Stir all the ingredients together. Drop spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook small slices of chicken in margarine until done.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.
Add 1/3 cup cooking wine and simmer a few minutes.
Good with rice.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sprinkle flour over white cake mix.
Add Jell-O, salad oil, water and frozen strawberries, thawed to mushy stage.
Mix thoroughly with electric beater.
Add 1 egg at a time until all 4 eggs have been added.
Divide batter into 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare cauliflower into flowerets.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing.
Mix into flowerets.
Marinate overnight.
Add sliced cucumbers and radishes just before serving.

title: rockin' roller nibbles
directions: Slice bananas into blender and puree.
In a bowl, combine bananas, cashews, coconut, oats, peanuts and sunflower seeds. Spread mixture evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle oil evenly over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir mixture to separate, then bake 10 minutes longer.
Stir again. Bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool.
Stir in raisins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to pkg using 1 stick butter. Mix rice with corn, soup, and 1/2 cheese. Bake 350° for 20 min. Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: creamy cabbage soup
directions: In a large 3 quart pan, cook cabbage, onions and celery in water until tender.
Add milk and soup.
Add seasoning of your choice.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vinegar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Mix and stir until it starts to thicken.
Pour into two 9 x 9-inch pans or onto a cookie sheet.
Cut when cool.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove bay leaf and cloves.
In a large frying pan, melt margarine.
Mix in flour. Add tomato mixture slowly, stirring constantly to prevent lumps. Cook until thickened and smooth. Add beans and heat.

title: my husband's favorite pie
directions: Mix first 6 items together. Peel apples and slice into thick slices. Put apples in pastry shell and pour mixture over them. Then cover with pastry strips. Put butter and sugar on top. Place in oven and bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Turn temperature down to 350° and cook until apples are done.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Beat sugar and egg yolks.
Mix part of flour with the fruit and nuts to coat them.
Combine the dry ingredients and wet ingredients (except egg whites).
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans which are lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° (slow oven).
(Bake large loaf about 1 hour or small loaves about 1/2 hour.
Check these often to prevent loaf from becoming too dark and drying out.)

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted margarine.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.

title: honey bars
directions: Beat well sugar, oil, honey and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In boiling water, cook the meat, celery, onion and garlic for 30 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, succotash and okra.
Add seasonings, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on a medium heat for 30 minutes more.
Peel and cut potatoes into large cubes; cook until tender.
Add the juice; simmer for another 15 to 20 minutes. (You can add the juice at the same time as the potatoes, if desired.)
Serve over steamed rice.

title: apricot ham steak
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove any fat around ham slice.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and stud sides with cloves.
Drain apricot syrup.
Pour 1/3 over ham.
Bake 1 hour, basting often, adding more syrup if needed.
Arrange drained apricots on top of ham and bake 15 minutes longer or until richly glazed.
Serves 6.

title: olive meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, pizza sauce, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape about 1 tablespoon of meat mixture evenly around each olive to form round meatballs.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Add rest of ingredients to soup and milk.
Stir well.
Put crushed chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(Mix in casserole dish.)

title: grandma's eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Place in 2 large mixing bowls.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar to each bowl.
Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and deep yellow in color.
Add brandy.
Stir well.
Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff, but not dry.
Fold beaten whites into yolk mixture.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon eggnog into punch cups.
Lightly sprinkle top of each with nutmeg.

title: easy meat dish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking casserole and put in the oven. Bake in oven for 3 hours at 325°.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Put corn and milk in blender and blend well.
Add egg yolks and parsley flakes.
Add cracker crumbs.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
(Cracker crumbs are salty.)
Mixture should be thick, not soupy.

title: tupperware fix and mix
directions: Mix and raise 30 minutes.
Divide into 4 parts put into pans and raise and bake @ 350 degrees.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Stir in soup, milk and parsley and simmer, covered for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook pasta, drain and put in baking dish.
Arrange chicken pieces on top, cover with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 400° uncovered about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spicy mexican skillet chicken
directions: Mix chili powder, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle evenly over both sides of chicken.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken in oil 10 minutes until brown on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes or until juice of chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut and vegetables are heated through.
Yields 4 servings.

title: swiss veggie medley
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions; place in covered casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Top with onions; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: amish country funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs with milk, gradually beat in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder until very smooth.

Holding the opening of the funnel closed with your fore-finger, fill the funnel with batter. Controlling the flow with your fore-finger, dribble the batter into hot oil, starting at the center of pan and swirling batter outward in a circle.
Fry 2 or 3 minutes or until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen cakes, depending on size.

title: 7-up red satin punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
Prepare 7-Up cubes or freeze 7-Up mold.
At serving time, combine cranberry
juice and apple juice in punch bowl.
Slowly pour 7-Up into bowl.
Add frozen cubes or frozen mold.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: *I use the new fat-free Carnation Coffee-mate.

title: egg noodles
directions: Combine eggs and salt.
Beat well.
Add butter and flour, mix into soft ball.
Divide into two parts.
Roll out on floured board. Roll thin and cut into strips.
Let dry and cook in chicken broth.

title: cheese ball #2
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: jalapeno bits
directions: Grease 8-inch pan with Wesson oil.
Line with sliced jalapenos.
Grate cheese and add to beaten eggs.
Pour over jalapenos.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let set for 10 minutes. Cut into small squares.

title: cream cheese puff
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and almond extract.
In another bowl, combine butter and vanilla.
Flatten biscuits into 3-inch diameter circles. Dip cream cheese pieces in butter mix, then in sugar mix.
Place in center of each biscuit and fold biscuit. Dip in sugar mix and place in ungreased muffin pan, seam side down. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: company onion soup
