directions: In a Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat. Saute onions until tender. Sprinkle sugar over onions. Reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are caramelized, about 20 minutes. Add 3 cups broth; simmer 15 minutes. Add remaining broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Fry onions, garlic and celery in oil, using a large pan.
Add ground beef.
Stir and cook until redness in meat disappears.
Add pepper, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and salt.
Simmer at least 20 minutes.
Skim off excess fat.

title: quaker oat bran muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk, egg whites, honey and oil, mixing just until moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups almost full.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Store muffins in freezer.
To reheat, microwave on High about 30 seconds.

title: cabbage au gratin casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water 10 minutes.
Drain and put in shallow baking dish or pan.
Blend milk, soup and cheese. Pour on cabbage.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes (or until hot).
Makes about 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, eggs, Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in broccoli and put in baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yeast bread
directions: Heat sugar, oil and salt in milk to lukewarm.
Let cool and add yeast that has been dissolved in warm water.
Work in the flour and leave in bowl.
Cover with a cloth and let rise to double in size. Pour out on floured board and knead.

title: mom's famous chili(fast and easy)
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes or until done or place in crock-pot or low until ready to serve.

title: sugarless applesauce
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook apples, soda and cinnamon until apples are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: best-ever apple pie filling
directions: Dissolve 5 ounces cinnamon red hots in 1 cup very hot water. Add 1 cup raisins and let stand while preparing rest of pie. Peel, core and slice apples. Mix sugar, nutmeg and allspice. Pour over sliced apples and mix well. Add cinnamon red hots/raisins mixture. Stir well and pour into 2 prepared pie crusts. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour over each pie filling. Cut 1 tablespoon margarine over each pie filling. Add top crust to each pie. Bake in preheated 400° oven 40 to 50 minutes or until done. Makes 8 servings.

title: squash-mushroom casserole
directions: Mash squash, stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: harkey's casserole(serves 12)
directions: Cook meat and onions in butter until done.
Mix rice, olives and mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese over top after combining all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to heat through.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in roaster and add 2 sliced onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown the 1 chopped onion in oil and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Cover pan and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and roast for 20 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry cream cheese shortbread
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in a 2-quart bowl. Microwave on High 3 1/2 minutes.
Take out and stir in peanuts. Microwave on High 9 minutes.
Take out and add butter, vanilla and coloring.
Stir 5 to 7 minutes and pour in buttered pans.
Sets up fast.
Makes 2 pie pans.

title: snowballs (cookies)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Form into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 225°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream, vanilla, flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour half of the batter in greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Cover with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool some and remove from pan.
Store in tight container.
Best made day before.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together; form into small balls (should make 60).
Roll each ball lightly in flour and brown, using 2 tablespoons hot Crisco.
Drain.

title: mexicali vegetable-beef soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, brown beef with onions, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twin casseroles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; saute until tender.
Stir in milk and cheese until smooth.
Add corn, pimentos, mushroom soup, salt, pepper and cooked noodles.
Divide mixture into two 1 1/2-quart dishes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Freezes well.
Bake until bubbly and tan colored.

title: caramel and pecan monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In pan, bring 1 cup sugar, butter and vanilla to boil.
In greased Bundt pan, place coated dough. Sprinkle pecans occasionally.
Pour in syrup.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown the chops.
Make the stuffing by combining the first 5 ingredients.
Put browned chops in casserole dish.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend the soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over all of the chops and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (You may use Stove Top stuffing in place of making your own.)

title: easter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla wafers, eggs and milk.
Mix together.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cut peppers, onions and celery into chunks and fry until golden brown.
Cook hamburger.
Mix noodles, soups and mushrooms together.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Chop mushrooms small (mixture should be spreadable).
Sprinkle with pinch of salt and butter.
Mix cheese with Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder (or fresh chopped garlic).
Spread filling on slices of bread and make sandwich.
Cut into serving size pieces and grill (as grilled cheese sandwiches).
Cut in fourths or larger (to taste).

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain and set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Combine 2 meats and cheese, stirring until the cheese melts.
Add spices.
Place bread on cookie sheet and spoon the mixture on each slice.
Place under broiler to brown.

title: snap, crackle and pop chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and butter.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and then roll in crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes crispy fried chicken.

title: shortcake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour to cream mixture and milk.
Bake in muffin pan for 10 minutes. Top with fruit and whipped cream.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Thaw berries.
Combine with sugar, egg whites, salt and juice. Beat until stiff (15 minutes).
Fold in whipped cream and almonds.
Mound in pie shell.
Freeze until firm.

title: luscious lemon dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend with flour and
nuts (pecans).
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken in a covered skillet until cooked through, but not browned; shred with fork. Put about 1/2 cup water and 1/3 package dry taco seasoning in skillet on top of chicken; mix well. Let this simmer covered until most of the water is gone. In an 8 x 11 baking pan, pour about 1/3 can of green chili enchilada sauce; cover with tortillas. Tear tortillas to fit in pan without overlapping. Spread 1/2 chicken mixture, 1/2 of chopped onion, 1/2 tomatoes and jalapenos, 1/2 stewed tomatoes and 1/3 of cheese over the tortillas. Pour remaining enchilada sauce from first can over this. Starting with tortillas, layer everything again, reserving 1/3 of cheese and 2/3 second can of enchilada sauce. Cover with final layer of tortillas and spoon remaining enchilada sauce over tortillas; don't leave any dry places. Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° until hot. Mix remaining dry taco seasoning with sour cream and serve on the side.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Shred cucumbers and onion in food processor.
Add buttermilk, cucumber dressing and add sour cream to thicken the mixture to desired consistency.
Add chives and parsley.
Add sugar to sweeten to individual taste.
Chill in refrigerator.
Thickens as it chills.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: finger paint
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Add flour. Stir over low heat until thick and shiny. Remove from heat.
Mix in an equal amount of liquid starch.
Add food coloring as desired.
Paint away the day.

title: crusted corn
directions: Combine all ingredients until blended.
Spread into greased 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Spray casserole pan with Pam. Tear up bread; pour the browned sausage over the bread and mix eggs with milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over bread and sausage.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cook for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
(Best to prepare the night before and cook in the morning.)

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening until light and fluffy; gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar, then beat in eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and nutmeg; alternately add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.

title: "fallen methodist" plant food
directions: Add tea, ammonia, shampoo and Miracle Grow to one gallon of water and mix; then add the gelatine and whiskey mixture.
Shake or mix until dissolved.
Use weekly.

title: holiday delight
directions: Crumble cake in bottom of dish.
Mix pudding and milk together and blend in 1 carton of whipped cream topping.
Pour over cake. Spoon crushed pineapple over mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans. Spread other carton of whipped topping and then sprinkle coconut all over.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust with the egg yolks.
Bake on cookie sheet about 5 minutes.
Remove crust from oven and reduce the heat to 350°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Layer in order given in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avocado dip or guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients except avocado together; not more than 1/2 an hour before serving.
Cut avocado; scrape skin well and mash. Mix into tomato mixture.
Squeeze lemon over top of mixture to prevent discoloration and wrap tightly.
To serve, pour off extra lemon and edge with tostados.

title: joggin in the jug
directions: Old time remedy to help cholesterol blood pressure.
Just makes you feel better.
Take 1/2 cup each morning.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Combine noodles, chicken, chicken broth, milk, salt and pepper in 2 quart microproof casserole.
Stir; cover with casserole lid and cook on 70 for 8-10 minutes or until noodles are cooked but still firm, stirring once.
Stir in cheese and olives.
Cook, uncovered, on 20 for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
4-6 servings.
Total cooking time: 13-15 minutes.

title: nut balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° to 325°.
When done, roll in powdered sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add soda; stir well.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet. Bake 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread onto waxed paper to dry.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers and onions with the salt.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Don't wash off salt.
Mix together vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and powdered alum; add by pouring over cucumbers.
Mix real good.
Let stand 1 week.
Can be kept in refrigerator.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, drain. Slice into 1/8 inch to 1/4 inch slices. Add onions, garlic and salt to cucumbers, cover with ice, mix well and allow to stand for 3 hours. Drain thoroughly and remove garlic. Combine sugar, spices and vinegar, heat just to a boil. Add cucumbers and onion slices and heat 5 minutes. Pack loosely into clean, hot pint-sized canning jars. Adjust lids and process in boiling water bath canner for 5 minutes. Yield: 7 pints.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Rub into fine crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture to sprinkle over the top.
To the remaining crumbs, add baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs to the sour milk and stir into the dry mixture; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and sprinkle crumbs over top.
Sprinkle an additional 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Top with chopped nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° in large cake pan until done.
Great with chili.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a shallow baking pan, skin side down. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, until chicken is golden brown.
Baste every 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: microwave chicken-mexican style
directions: Mix salt, pepper, crumbs and taco seasoning.
Place in a Ziploc bag.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time to coat.
Place on microwave safe dish in a circle.
Cover with paper towel and cook on 100% power for approximately 20 minutes.
(Microwave temperatures vary in different brands.)
Check for doneness.
If necessary, rotate chicken and cook 5 minutes longer.
Allow to stand a few minutes, uncovered, after cooking before serving.

title: chicken roll snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl combine chicken, parsley, 2 tablespoons crushed croutons, curry powder, mayonnaise and onion.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Press or roll each to form 10 x 5-inch rectangle.
Spread 1/4 of the chicken mixture on each rectangle within 1/2 inch of edge.
Starting at longest side, roll up; pinch seams to seal.
Cut each roll into 3 pieces.
Dip each piece in butter then croutons.
Place seam side down on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Stir in milk
and
melted butter or
margarine.
Pour into greased
3-quart
casserole. Bake in 400° oven 1 hour, stirring twice.

title: chicken green tomato tortillas
directions: Boil fryer in water until tender.
Cut up in small pieces.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Chop apples and cranberries very fine in food chopper.
Mix sugar, orange juice, pineapple, apples and cranberries and set aside for 30 minutes.
Add nuts if desired.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Let cool, then spoon fruit mixture into Jell-O. Refrigerate overnight.
Make this the night before serving.
This salad may be molded or put into an oblong container and sliced into serving portions.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat eggs slightly. Beat in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.

title: diet meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 2 loaves.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: schnapps
directions: Boil water and sugar and let cool.
Add vodka and extract. Mix. Drink.

title: nutty slaw salad
directions: Break up Ramen noodles before combining with chopped cabbage, onions, toasted almonds and sesame seeds.

title: corn flake critters
directions: Combine sugar and syrup together and heat in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: green onion dressing
directions: Blend all together and fold in 3 tablespoons parsley flakes, dill or garlic.
Chill before serving.

title: different chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites and add sugar gradually.
Fold in vanilla, nuts and graham crackers.
Spread in an ungreased 9-inch round pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips immediately.
Cool and add whipped topping.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Mix together ketchup, sugar and barbecue sauce.
Wrap each water chestnuts in 1/2 slice bacon.
Secure with a toothpick. Bake in oven on cookie sheet at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Drain grease from cookie sheet.
Pour sauce over water chestnuts and cook additional 15 minutes.

title: green frost punch
directions: Blend sugar and Kool-Aid.
Add grapefruit drink and 6 cups cold water and lemon juice.
Add half of sherbet.
Scoop 1/2 of sherbet on top.
Gently pour carbonated pop.
Gently stir inward from side of bowl.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well. Add vanilla and buttermilk. Sift and add the flour, sugar, soda, salt and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: please don't feed the animals
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 6 cups.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine veggies, soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 onions. Pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onion. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: oven stew
directions: In 3-quart or larger baking dish, layer first 5 ingredients. In small bowl, combining remaining ingredients.
Mash tomatoes with fork; pour over first ingredients.
Do not stir.
Put in preheated oven at 350°.
DO NOT OPEN OVEN for 2 hours.
Full time: 3 to 4 hours.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: wyatt's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil until tender, about 30 minutes. Mix together crumbs and milks and add to vegetables that have been sauteed in the oleo.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese). Bake in greased casserole dish 35 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Heat through, but do not brown.
Spread in large baking dish 3 cups of cabbage and 1/2 meat mixture.
Pour soup over the top.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon; reserve fat.
Tear bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Wash and tear the spinach into bite size pieces.
Add bacon, chopped eggs, diced onion, shredded Swiss cheese and garlic croutons. Blend remaining ingredients together for a dressing.
Best if dressing is made and refrigerated a day in advance.
When ready to serve, drizzle 3 tablespoons bacon fat on spinach.
Add dressing and toss.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples; slice into pieces.
Put into pan with other ingredients.
Cook apples until very soft, using potato masher to press apples into sauce.
Add cinnamon to taste; can adjust sugar to individual's taste.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and cook cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch holes in hot cake.
Mix can of cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix together and pour over hot cake.
Let cool and then frost with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
Let cake sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together except pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put pecans on top and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375°; bake until firm in center.

title: black and white macadamia pie
directions: Crust:
Mix together with wire whisk until crumbly the flour, butter and 1/2 cup chopped Macadamia nuts.
Press into greased (Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: yum-yums
directions: Cream butter and sugar well, add water.
Stir in flour and salt.
Spread in pan and bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: roast
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Wash roast in cool water.
Marinate roast overnight in Zesty Italian dressing.
Add pepper.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: healthy eggplant parmesan
directions: Drain juice from the tomatoes into a mixing bowl. Chop the tomatoes and add to bowl.
Stir in garlic and herbs.
Peel and thinly slice the eggplant into rounds.
Spoon just enough of the tomato sauce to thinly coat the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange half of the eggplant over the sauce.
Sprinkle half of the bread crumbs over the eggplant. Spoon all of the Ricotta evenly on top.
Cover with half of the Mozzarella and half of the Parmesan cheese.
Spoon half of the remaining tomato sauce over the cheeses.
Repeat the eggplant, bread crumbs, Mozzarella, Parmesan and tomato layers.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until eggplant is tender.
Serve hot with Italian bread and a green salad.

title: beef thing
directions: Cook in pot with a tight lid or put foil over a casserole dish and then put cover on top of foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours. Do not peek while it bakes.
Before serving, add the sour cream and serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: easy roast and gravy
directions: Mix and pour over roast.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Thicken gravy, if desired.
Delicious.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Knead and work together with hands until batter is well blended.
Roll into small balls, using about 1 teaspoon dough.
Place onto an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a glass that has been buttered and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: scotch potatoes
directions: Fry bacon in heavy skillet until crisp, remove to warm dish and set aside.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water. Drain, reserving liquid.
Melt butter. Add onion and cook until soft (transparent but do not brown).
Blend in flour. Add broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups reserved liquid (adding water if necessary to make 1 1/2 cups).
Add cream, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Add broccoli.
Heat to boiling. Stir in cheese.
Serve sprinkled with chopped chives or parsley. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together carrot, oil and eggs; add sugar.
Mix very well with electric mixer.
In separate bowl mix all dry ingredients, then
add slowly to first mixture.
Use 2 (8 inch) round pans, a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 large bread loaf pans.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 325° for one hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add remaining ingredients, beating well.
Place in ungreased, unfloured Bundt pan and bake for 90 minutes.

title: cheese pecan roll
directions: Combine all ingredients in order named, except pecans.
Form in rolls about 2-inches in diameter.
Roll in chopped pecans and in oiled paper.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well and flavor improves. Slice as needed.

title: lornes (scottish recipe)
directions: Mix all together and chill in freezer about 24 hours.
Slice and fry.
(Tastes like pork sausage.)

title: damn good leg of lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Massage creme de menthe into the flesh of the lamb.
Place in a roaster.
Sprinkle top with salt, pepper and mint.
In a small mixing bowl, beat olive oil, Worcestershire sauce, wine and mustard.
Pour into bottom of roaster around the meat.
Spread onion over top.
Cover and bake for 2 hours, basting occasionally, until done.
Remove lid and bake another 15 to 30 minutes to brown meat.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken, bone and set aside.
Saute onion in 1/2 stick of oleo.
Add green chilies, Cheez Whiz, soup and sour cream.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Put 2 tablespoons mixture on tortilla, 3 tablespoons (more or less) chicken on tortilla and roll up.
Place in a long baking dish and when filled, pour remaining soup mixture over and top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: shake-a-sack cracker snack
directions: In a lunch size paper sack or plastic bag, combine the cheese crackers, oyster crackers, pretzels, dry salad dressing mix and dill weed. Close bag and shake well. Pour oil into sack and shake again. Store in airtight container.

title: dumplins
directions: Put flour in large bowl. Make hole in center of flour, then add remaining ingredients in hole. Use fork and work together until stiff. Divide. Put half out on floured surface. Knead flour in until workable. Roll out thin and cut into desired size. Have broth boiling; add 3 to 4 bouillon cubes and 2 to 3 tablespoons margarine. Then drop in dumplins.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish in a 350° oven or in microwave.
In a mixing bowl mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk with a spoon.
Pour over melted margarine; do not stir.
Put fruit over all; do not stir.
Put dish in 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Prepare jello according to package instructions.
Let jello cool.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into oiled mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix all in blender.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Mix together noodles, mushroom soup, peas, and tuna.
Place in a casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on the top.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Combine all other ingredients.
Mix with spinach.
Cut the top of the bread and hollow out to form a bowl.
Cube the removed bread into bite-sized chunks.
Pour the dip into bread "bowl" and serve with bread chunks.

title: munchy crunchies
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Melt chips and peanut butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir to blend.
Remove from heat.
Add noodles and marshmallows; stir to coat.
Using two forks, drop mounds of the mixture onto the waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill until set.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 15.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: chili con carne
directions: Put beef in heavy skillet and cook until meat is lightly browned.
Drain fat.
Stir in other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: quick cookies
directions: Make into balls (a teaspoon).
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: brake light cherry bread
directions: Mix in order listed and let stand 2 minutes.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add fish and cook 2 minutes more. Beat eggs, cream and seasoning.
Add cheese, fish and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: barbara bush's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add the oats, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift and add flour, soda and salt.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Mix coloring and cocoa. Add to mixture, beating well.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately beating well after each addition.
Mix soda and vinegar and fold into mixture.
Bake in 3- 9 in. greased and floured pans at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
The cake is done when it pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Do not overbake.
Let cake cool in pans then on racks for 10 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Melt butter and pour in warm milk with the sugar and salt. Add 2 cups flour and beat in mixer for 5 minutes at medium speed. Stop mixer and add yeast; beat another minute.
Add beaten egg and another 1 1/4 cups flour.
(Add more milk if needed.)
Beat another 10 minutes.
Let rise in bowl for about 1 hour in a warm place.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Remove dough from bowl and press down into pan.
Smooth with tablespoon that has been dipped in melted butter.
Cut in squares, then let rise for 30 minutes. Bake in 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, parsley and sliced olives.
Spread generously on 3 slices of bread; cover with other 3 slices.
Cut each sandwich into 4 triangles each; arrange points up into a greased 8-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs with remaining ingredients; pour evenly over all the triangles, moistening each one well. Bake at 350° until nicely set and lightly browned, approximately 35 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine cocoa, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in boiling water.
Stir over medium heat until smooth and slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Store in refrigerator in airtight jar.

title: cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into small pieces.
Melt butter and add flour until pasty. Add milk and broth. Cook over medium heat until mixed well.
Add chicken and serve over rice.

title: my chili sauce
directions: Stir often, cook about 3 hours.
Taste often for right flavors.

title: low-fat sugar dessert
directions: In a boiler, bring pineapple to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in jello; mix well.
Pour into a bowl, stir in buttermilk. Store in refrigerator.
Low-fat Cool Whip may be added when served.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheets with Pam and place 2 rolls on each pan to thaw.
When dough is thawed, stretch out to approximately 6-inches in diameter.
Place 3 to 4 pepperoni slices in middle along with a large pinch of cheese.
Roll up in cabbage roll fashion.
Place back on cookie sheet to rise.
When double in size, bake in 350° oven for approximately 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: grape souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of gelatin into 3-quart mold; chill.
Add sour cream to remaining gelatin; whip with electric mixer until fluffy.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir in sugar, pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Chill until ready to use.
Just before serving, spoon in sherbet and pour ginger ale over.
Serves 40.

title: pasta alla teresa
directions: Begin boiling water for pasta.
Heat butter and oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Saute garlic for 1 minute.
Cut Prosciutto and sundried tomatoes into thin julienne strips, stir into skillet with pine nuts and shrimp.
Saute for 2 minutes. Stir in cream, nutmeg, pepper and Parmesan cheese, bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer over very low heat while cooking pasta.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Bake, boil or fry chicken; set aside.
Saute onions, oregano, basil, salt and pepper in margarine or butter.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 cup water; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: In saucepan, cover carrots with water; add salt and cook until tender. Drain. Combine with margarine in blender or processor. Process until smooth. Add sugar, baking powder, flour, eggs and vanilla in bowl. Mix. Add carrot mixture. Mix well. Spoon into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: zucchini beef soup
directions: In large pan, cook beef, celery, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Drain if greasy.
Stir in rest of the ingredients and spices.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20-25 minutes.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Cut up hot dogs and marinate overnight.
Cook slow and simmer several hours.

title: angel wings
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll into small ball and dip in cold water and then sugar. Place sugar side up on cookie sheet. Bake 325 degrees for approx. 8-10 minutes or golden brown.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Mix pasta, celery, green pepper, carrot and onion in a bowl.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Place potatoes in casserole dish. Mix in soup, sour cream, onions and cheese.
Mix together 1/2 stick margarine, softened and 1 cup of corn flakes.
Sprinkle over top of potato mixture.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in roasting pan and bake at 275° for five hours.

title: whole cranberry sauce
directions: Boil sugar and water until a thin syrup.
Wash and drain berries.
Drop into hot syrup and simmer gently, keeping covered until berries are clear, transparent and tender.
The cooking must be gentle or berries will come to pieces.
The beauty of this sauce is the whole clear berry.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix oleo, confectioners sugar, Rice Krispies and peanut butter together, then shape in small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax together in double boiler.
Roll peanut butter balls in chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.
Keep refrigerated.

title: four bean casserole baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck with chopped pepper and onion.
Combine all ingredients, cook on low for 30 minutes or bake at 325 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown meat in small amounts of fat and when brown, sprinkle with garlic salt and put in a casserole dish.
Add seasoning and drained mushrooms with some liquid.

title: crock-pot "special beef"
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: carrot date bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mixed dry ingredients.
Add balance of ingredients.
Put in lightly greased and floured 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Line serving bowl with lettuce leaves.	Chill mixture for several hours before adding chow mein noodles.
Pour onto lettuce leaves and serve.

title: texas broccoli and rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter in saucepan until tender. Combine soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Break broccoli apart with fork.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add salt, pepper and onion mixture. Mix well. Place in buttered casserole.
Refrigerate for 12 hours. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: aunt lee's red velvet cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vinegar to eggs.
Add flour and soda, alternately with buttermilk. Blend ingredients well.
Then add vanilla and cake coloring. Pour batter into 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Combine fruit, coconut and marshmallows with sour cream.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: crock-pot mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and drain water.
Mash potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight or put in crock-pot directly.
If refrigerated, allow at least 3 hours on low setting of crock-pot.

title: braised celery
directions: Combine ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes or until celery is tender.

title: biscochitos
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl cream lard and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, anise and brandy extract.
Beat and mix well. Add flour alternately, with baking powder, salt and creamed mixture until stiff dough has formed.
Knead dough; pat or roll out to 1/4-inch shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, gelatin (diluted) and eggs and oil.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Bake according to directions on cake mix box in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Immediately after removing it from oven, poke holes in top of cake with a fork.
Pour thawed strawberries over cake.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: mincemeat nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; stir in walnuts.
In mixing bowl, beat egg, stir in mincemeat, oil and orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix to blend.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Chill before slicing. Yield:
1 loaf.

title: italian rice
directions: Brown beef, onion, bell pepper, salt, chili powder, pepper and garlic juice.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and rice.
Place in baking dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve with green salad and hot bread for excellent meal.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of the milk in top of double boiler, stirring until smooth.
Set aside.

title: basic omelet
directions: In 9-inch pie plate, place butter and oil.
Microwave at High 30 to 45 seconds until melted.
Turn plate to coat bottom with butter and oil.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Cook chicken in water and add onion.
Boil until tender and falling off the bone.
Remove chicken from liquid and take off the bone.
Strain liquid.
Add carrots, chicken, salt and pepper to liquid and bring to a boil.
Drop biscuit dough by the tablespoons into hot liquid.
Simmer about 30 minutes, stirring frequently, until dough is cooked through and carrots are tender.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine
chicken,
picante sauce, onion, cumin, oregano and salt
in
a
saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes or until most of liquid has evaporated.
Brush 1 side of tortillas with butter. Spoon about
cup
of
chicken
mixture
onto
center
of unbuttered sides.
Top
with
tablespoons of cheese.
Fold down sides over filling; fold ends down.
Place seam side down in
x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 475° for 13 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.
Top with guacamole, additional picante sauce and sour cream to serve.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon.
When crisp, drain and crumble.
Add vinegar and sugar in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cubed potatoes. Add cut up eggs and onion; serve hot.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour hot water over cornmeal.
Add sugar, egg yolks (beaten), melted shortening and last, stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for about 30 minutes.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce, oil, sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Marinate carrots, onions and pepper in this mixture overnight.
Combine all ingredients into a bowl with lettuce (your choice) and serve leftover marinade as dressing over the lettuce salad.

title: baked chicken
directions: Take skin off of fryer. Salt, pepper and lemon pepper chicken. Put in a 9 x 13 pan. Cook at 375°. After 20 minutes, brush with margarine and cook until brown. Turn and brush with margarine and cook for 20 more minutes. Continue to do this until chicken is done.

title: yam delight
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and 2 sticks of margarine (melted) together and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour and cheese; mix well.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Place the apples in greased square baking dish; spread butter cheese mixture over apples with spatula.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed loaf cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add poppy seed, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with half and half, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 1 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until wooden pick in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Pour glaze over cake and cool completely.

title: caramel icing
directions: Dissolve and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. If too thick, add more milk.

title: kibbeh nayye(raw kibbi)
directions: Make Kibbeh according to directions, using 2 cups burghul instead of 3.
After final kneading, place on a large oval platter and spread it out flat.
Round the edges and smooth the top, using hand dipped in iced water.
Make a depression in the center with thumb and with the side of forefinger make 2 grooves along and across kibbeh to the edges.
Alternately shape on individual dishes.

title: caramel corn chex
directions: Boil together for 1 1/2 minutes the oleo, brown sugar and Karo. Add 1/2 teaspoon soda. Pour over Corn Chex in a brown bag. Microwave for 4 minutes. Shake bag after each minute. Spread on wax paper to cool. Store in Ziploc bag.

title: savory chuck roast(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Rub roast with vinegar. Cut 8 to 10 slits in roast; sprinkle garlic salt into slits. Dredge roast in flour. Brown roast on all sides in hot oil. Stir together soup mix, sherry, coffee, 1 cup water and mushrooms; pour over roast. Heat until warmed. Bake, covered, at 350° for 3 hours or until roast is fork-tender.

title: grilled ginger-lime pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloin in leakproof plastic bag or nonmetallic baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over meat and marinate at least 4 hours in refrigerator.
Remove meat from marinade; pat dry.
Reserve marinade.
Grill over low fire for 40 minutes, turning and basting with marinade.
Cook until meat thermometer reads between 145° and 160°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Combine pineapple, lime juice and cloves.
Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness; add to marinade.
Cover and refrigerate for 45 minutes.
Drain; reserve marinade.
Combine flour and salt; dredge chicken.
Brown on both sides in oil.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Add reserved marinade to skillet; cook until hot.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds and coconut.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple fritters(applewood farms, sevierville, tennessee)
directions: Beat egg.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk, egg and melted margarine.
Add orange juice, rind, chopped apples (skins may be left on) and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into milk mixture with a spoon until blended.
Do not overmix!
Preheat oil in a skillet to 350°.
Drop off end of tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown.
Turn so they brown evenly.
Allow to cool.

title: almond in haystack
directions: Combine ham, 4 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup salad dressing, 1/2 cup almonds (chopped), 1/3 cup onions and pickle relish.
Mix well and chill.
Shape as desired.
Combine 1/4 cup salad dressing and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Frost ham appetizer.
Chill slightly.
Cover with almonds and serve with crackers.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Melt butter.
Add chicken and cook until done.
Remove chicken.
Stir flour into drippings.
Cook 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and cream.
Stir and cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in mustard.
Return chicken and cover for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix well, making sure all of the ingredients are equally mixed. Fry by the spoonful in deep fat.

title: bierocks
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and chill for several hours.
Brown beef and onion in skillet, add cabbage, pepper and Tabasco.
Cover skillet.
Continue cooking over low heat, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender.
Cool slightly.
Roll out dough into thin sheets, cut in 5-inch squares.
Place 2 tablespoons meat mixture on each square.
Pinch edges together and place pinched sides down on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Fry bacon, then saute onion in bacon grease to soften.
Place green beans in baking dish. Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Stir. Crumble fried bacon on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: peanut butter tempters
directions: Combine and drop ingredients with a tablespoon on cookie sheet (do not grease cookie sheet).
Bake 15 minutes at 325°. Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen cookies.

title: red lobster cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine first three ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine margarine or butter and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: candied crust apple pie
directions: Spread apples evenly in a 9-inch heat-resistant glass pie plate.
Combine dry ingredients and cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Watch as pie may bubble over.
Top with ice cream before serving.

title: cornmeal bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Combine beaten egg, sour milk and melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir lightly and pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown turkey with onion and then add taco seasoning with water.
Take biscuits and put a layer of those on greased casserole dish, then layer meat mixture, then top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done and then serve.

title: peanut butter pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown and white sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, salt and soda.
Roll dough out to 1/4-inch thick in an oblong shape.
Spread with the melted chocolate chips.
Roll up the dough on a sheet of waxed paper and refrigerate.
(In rolling up the dough, it's a little hard to get it started, but persevere.)
After the dough is chilled, slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in well-greased hot skillet.
Bake until firm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and coat dish.
Put layer of stuffing mix on bottom.
Mix sour cream, soup and onion with squash.
Pour into dish.
Put light layer of stuffing mix on top.
Pour rest of butter on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tortilla snacks
directions: Soften cream cheese, then mix with Hidden Valley Ranch mix, calling for milk.
Spread onto tortillas.
Sprinkle chopped onions, chopped celery, red pepper and black olives on top of cream cheese.
Roll tightly.
Chill 2 hours or overnight in a covered container.
Cut
off ends and roll them into half-inch pieces.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and cream good.
Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream, flavorings and orange juice.
Mix good.
Add cranberries, orange rind and nuts; mix well.
Makes 7 small aluminum foil pans or 3 large loaves.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes for small pans or for 50 to 60 minutes for large loaf pans.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Pare and cut potatoes into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil in a large pot until a fork easily pierces cubes.
Drain and place in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle granulated sugar and brown sugar over potatoes.
Slice butter into several "pats" and place evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Poke holes all over top of cake with fork. Combine milk, sugar and half of coconut in saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Carefully spoon over warm cake.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip and spread over cake.
According to your taste and love for coconut, you may sprinkle with more.
Chill overnight.
If you have any leftover cake, store in refrigerator.

title: cream gravy for chicken fried steak
directions: This gravy is to be made after frying chicken fried steak. Drain drippings from skillet leaving at least 3 T grease and the meat crumbs.
Stir in flour to moisten and cook a few minutes until flour begins to brown.
Gradually pour in milk, add salt and pepper and stir constantly until gravy thickens, about 5 minutes.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Blend
all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.	Makes 1 cup.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and pretzels; blend lightly.
Reserve 1 cup for top.
Press remaining mixture in baking dish.
Fold whipped topping into blended cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread 1/2 the cream cheese mixture on crust, then cherry pie filling, then remaining cream cheese.
Sprinkle remaining pretzels on top.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: broccoli lima bake
directions: Cook vegetables until crispy tender.
Blend sour cream, mushroom soup and onion soup mix together.
Fold into cooked vegetables and pour into buttered baking dish.
Push sliced chestnuts down into mixture edgewise.
Top with Rice Krispies that have been browned in butter.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt to full boil. Cook for two minutes, add soda.
Stir well.
Double this recipe and pour over popped corn.
Microwave on High 4 1/2 minutes. Shake bag every 1 1/2 minutes.
Let sit in bag to cool.
Shake again to break up.

title: kentucky hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add onions and buttermilk and finally the beaten egg.
Fry in moderately hot cooking oil until brown; turn only once.
Serves 4.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and salt and beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Add flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake about 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: flambeed pepper steak
directions: Crush green peppercorns in a mortar with a pestle.
Chop onion. Combine.
Press peppercorn mixture into meat on both sides.
In a skillet, heat butter until lightly brown.
Add steaks.
Brown well on one side.
Turn steaks over.
Brown other side.
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Remove steaks to a serving dish.
Cover.
Keep warm.
Add cream to skillet.
Scrape up brownings.
Cook until reduced.
Add beef consomme.
Strain liquid.
Set aside.
Rinse skillet.
Heat skillet again.
Add steaks.
Pour cognac over. Ignite.
Add cream mixture.
Let cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry and drain hamburger; drain and clean beans.
Mix both in large bowl and let cool at room temperature.
Add lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Just before serving, add dressing and chips.

title: "tropical carrot cake"
directions: Mix together baking soda, cinnamon and flour.
Cream together the oil and fructose (or whatever sweetener desired).
Beat in the eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in the carrots, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: halushki
directions: Mix flour, eggs and oil together, adding water as needed to make a dough.
Knead dough, then let set for 1/2 hour.
Roll dough out thin as size should double when cooked.
Cut with a knife or pizza cutter into noodle-like strips or cut into any other shapes or sizes desired.
Place dough cuts into a pan of boiling water and boil for 6 minutes; remove and drain.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic.
Cover with waxed paper and cook in microwave for 3 minutes.
Mix crumbs, Parmesan and parsley.
Dip chicken in egg and then in crumb mixture.

Cover with waxed paper and cook for 5 minutes. Rearrange chicken and cook for 4 to 9 minutes longer until opaque. Pour the sauce over the chicken and sprinkle with the Mozzarella. Cook for another 2 to 4 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream in small bowl and set aside. Mash potatoes thoroughly with mixer until smooth.	Add cream cheese mixture and beat well.
Stir in chives.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread
in
x
13-inch	buttered baking dish. Cover and
put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Before baking, dot with butter and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion together in a small amount of water for 3 minutes.
Mix all ingredients (except last 2) together.
Put in greased casserole.

title: 10-minute german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring in chocolate until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls.
Any left over can be stored in freezer.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add undrained strawberries, pineapple, and bananas.
Pour half mixture in mold and congeal thoroughly.
Spread sour cream over congealed mixture. Then add rest of mixture and let congeal.

title: garlic knots
directions: Cut pizza dough in strips and make a knot.
Put them on a cooking sheet and bake them until brown.
In a bowl, combine chopped garlic, olive oil, parsley, cheese, spices and salt. While bread is still hot, toss them in the bowl so they will be evenly coated and serve.

title: sausage green chili strata(breakfast)
directions: Crumble sausage, cook and drain.
Set aside.
Lightly butter the bread and cut into cubes.
Place half the bread cubes into bottom of greased 8-inch square pan or double recipe and use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half the cheese.
Cover with sausage.
Add remaining bread cubes and remaining cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasoning.
Pour over bread, cheese and sausage.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, drain chillies and sprinkle over.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange refrigerated crescent rolls on bottom of pan.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs.
Beat after each egg.
Add gradually all dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° to 350°.

title: wetha see byan (dry pork curry)(origin: burmese)
directions: Cut pork into 5 cm (2-inch) pieces.
Excess fat should be removed or the curry will be too rich, but a little fat left on the meat is quite acceptable.
Puree and cook onion, garlic, ginger, chili and turmeric.
When well cooked, add pork and simmer gently in its own juices until tender.
Add crushed or finely chopped lemon grass or rind, tamarind juice and fish sauce.
Stir well. Cook until all water has evaporated and the oil separates from the gravy.
The flavour of the curry can be varied by adding extra chili powder for a hot curry, or stirring in a piece of hot Indian mango pickle.
Slices of lemon, chopped fresh coriander leaves or chopped spring onions can be added at the end of cooking, if desired.

title: rich potato salad
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Pour over potatoes and toss.
Set aside to cool.
Add olives and rest of ingredients. Toss; chill.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Add ingredients.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lillian's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stuff mushrooms.
Cook slowly in butter until done.
If desired, stick under broiler until brown.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread one side of each piece of bread with the dressing or mustard.
Layer the corned beef, cheese and sauerkraut on one slice and top with the other slice.
Spread the outside of both sides with butter.
Grill both sides in a medium skillet on medium until light brown and the cheese is melted.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking soda, sugar and baking powder.
In a small bowl, add egg (slightly beaten) and milk.
Stir together and add to flour mixture.
(If batter is too thick, add small amount of milk.)
Beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel and pour in some batter.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into pan filled with 1-inch of hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve hot.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter or margarine.
Add vanilla and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: low calorie low fat breakfast casserole
directions: Cook- brown and drain turkey sausage and place in a 13x9-inch pan, sprayed with cooking spray.
In same fry pan, brown onion, green pepper, and mushrooms.
Adding broccoli after 5 minutes until vegetables are tender but not mushy.
Add vegetables to sausage and mix, add cheese and mix again, after add spices.
Pour over all a large container of egg substitute and mix gently.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean, if not browned you may want to put under the broiler for a few minutes, but watch carefully.
Cut in.
Serves 6-8.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat in frying pan.
When brown, drain meat. Place meat in big pot when drained.
Next fry onion in frying pan until tender, then place onion in with meat mixture.
Then add tomatoes and pork and beans.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with rolls or cornbread.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla extract.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips, sweet chocolate and walnuts.
Make balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: sunshine cake(a great holiday cake)
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Combine cracker crumbs and baking soda and add to first mixture.
When well mixed, add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into two 9-inch well-greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and frost with Pineapple Icing.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: raspberry delight
directions: In a bowl combine flour and sugar; blend butter till smooth. Press into ungreased baking pan 13 x 9 inches.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes

title: mother's prune pie
directions: Cook prunes with a little water.
Mash fine and add the chopped nuts.
Add the sugar to the beaten egg whites; beat well again.
Add the prune and nut mixture.
Put the prune stuff into a baked pastry shell.
Bake very slowly for about 25 minutes.
Serve with a generous dollop of real whipped cream.

title: mississippi mud cake(microwave)
directions: In 12 x 8-inch glass dish, place butter and cocoa.
Heat on High 2 minutes or until melted.
In large mixer bowl, place eggs. Beat slightly.
Add sugar, flour and butter/cocoa mixture.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Pour mixture into glass dish and microwave 7 to 9 minutes on High, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes.
Distribute marshmallows over top of hot cake and microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes until marshmallows are melted.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Makes 1 gallon powdered drink.
When serving to drink, add 1/4 cup of powdered mix to your cup of hot water (coffee cup).
Add a 1/2 teaspoon of more instant coffee for a mocha taste.
Makes a good drink for cold weather.

title: chicken shortcake
directions: Bake baking powder biscuits, split and spread with margarine. Fry onion and celery in oil until onions are soft and clear.
Stir in soup mixed with milk.
Heat and stir so it doesn't stick.
Add chicken.
Add peas.
Heat until hot only.
Add salt and pepper, if needed.
When the chicken is bubbly hot, spoon it between and on top of the biscuits.

title: english muffins o'yummies
directions: Mix 1st 4 ingredients and spread on muffin halves; cut into 4 or 6 wedges.
Put under broiler until bubbly.
Makes approx. 30 to 36 wedges.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large pot, saute ground beef.
Remove fat.
Add onions and garlic.
Lightly brown.
Add carrots, celery, tomato sauce, catsup, water, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 1 hour, stirring often.
Add Kluski noodles.
Simmer until noodles are done.

title: chinese noodle dish
directions: Fry ground meat until very light brown and drain well.
Mix together all ingredients except noodles.
Pour into baking dish or pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Spread noodles on top and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread beans into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth and spread over beans.
Add nacho sauce (if this seems too watery, drain).
Shred cheese and add on top of salsa.
Chop items and place over cheese.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: roast venison(crock-pot)
directions: Allow fresh or frozen venison to stand overnight in marinade in refrigerator.
Season with salt; roll in flour and brown in hot skillet.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low, 10 to 14 hours.

title: seafoam
directions: Chop nuts and have vanilla ready.
Boil brown sugar and water together until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Beat egg white until very stiff.
Pour boiling syrup or egg white a little at a time while beating constantly.
When getting a little stiff, add vanilla.
Add 1 cup nuts when mixture stands alone. Drop by spoonfuls on buttered dish and let cool.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Soften and combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.
Form into ball and roll in nuts.

title: elisabeth's lemon chicken
directions: In blender, combine juice of lemon (save the rind), olive oil, garlic, basil, thyme, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Place chicken in a plastic bag.
Pour "goop" inside and outside of chicken.
Shove the rinds inside the bird and seal bag with twistie.
Refrigerate for at least 1 day, but 2 is better. Remove rinds and place in roasting pan.
Pour remaining marinade over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Skim fat and pour goop over chicken and serve.

title: dirt and worms
directions: Make instant pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in a sand pail, clear bowl or small cups the Oreos, Cool Whip and worms; repeat.
Last layer Oreos on top with worms poking in and out. Great for parties or Halloween.

title: ambrosia(5 cup salad)
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl. Refrigerate for 4 hours, then serve.

title: honeysuckle chicken salad in cantaloupe
directions: Cut cantaloupe into halves, discarding seed.
Cut pulp into balls, reserving shells.
Combine chopped, cooked chicken with seedless green grapes, slivered almonds and mayonnaise in bowl. Fold in melon balls and honeysuckle blossoms.
Serve in drained cantaloupe shells.
Serves 4.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onions in boiling water (salted) for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and yogurt; stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Spread half of mixture on bottom of 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Save the juice.
It should take about 3 cups, if not, add water to make 3 cups.
Add the juice to the puddings and microwave until thick (cook about 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes).
Cool completely.
Combine the pudding mixture with the fruit, adding the bananas (if desired) and cherries last.
Could add other fruits, nuts, etc.

title: potato broccoli cheese soup
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 3/4-inch cubes; set aside.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; add onion and saute for 5 minutes. Add potatoes and water/broth.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook just until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove 1 cup of the potato cubes with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Pour contents of saucepan into a blender and mix until smooth, then return mixture to the saucepan.

title: grandma airhart's "tea cakes"
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients (sifted together) and liquids alternately.
Chill for several hours before rolling out.
When the dough is the desired thickness, sprinkle sugar over surface and roll lightly.
This dough can also be formed into a roll and frozen.
Slice into cookies; place on baking sheet and sprinkle with sugar. Temperature of oven and length of baking time depends on thickness of cookie.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Prepare baked pie shell.
Cook first three ingredients in top of double boiler over hot water until thick.
Add water slowly and let thicken again.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with rotary beater until egg yolks and whites are well blended.
Add granulated sugar and salt. Mix well.
Beat in two cans evaporated milk and add the vanilla. Put brown sugar in bottom of loaf pan and pour the custard gently into loaf pan over it.
Place in shallow baking pan container hot water, but not boiling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Do not cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, run a knife around the edge of pan and turn out onto a small platter.

title: cheesey mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes and season to your liking.
Add the onion powder, seasoning salt, and sour cream; mix.
Put half of the potatoes in a greased baking dish, then add some cheese and cracker crumbs.
Add the rest of the potatoes, and put remaining cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted and is heated through.
This can be made a day ahead, cover, and refrigerate.
Take out of refrigerator, and let sit at room temperature about a half hour before baking.

title: harvest pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes more.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown beef and pork together; drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Roll mixture in egg roll wraps.
Fry egg rolls in oil until brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Spread half of sauerkraut in baking dish. Place browned chops over kraut.
Layer half the soup and remaining kraut.
Finish with remaining soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: calico country soup
directions: Wash beans and cover with water.
Add salt and soak overnight. Drain beans and put in 2 quarts fresh water.
Add a ham bone and ham pieces.
Cook approximately 1 hour.
Add tomatoes and chilies, sugar, oregano, sage and chili powder.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer all together for another hour or until beans are done.
Serve with hot cornbread or corn muffins.

title: raspberry sherbet party punch
directions: Combine all in punch bowl.
Triple recipe for wedding.
Great in summer.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 1 hour; debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Mix cream soup and sour cream together; mix with chicken and pour into lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Mix crushed crackers, melted butter and poppy seed; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, approximately 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly in center.
Favorite!

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to the package directions.
Pour batter into two 9 x 13 baking pans so that cake will be thin; it is better to put wax paper in the bottom so you have something to turn it out with.
Bake until brown, but don't overbake.
When cake is cool, turn out onto a flat platter or baking sheet. Spread filling between layers.

title: make ahead macaroni frankfurter bake
directions: Fry bacon crisp; reserve 2 tablespoons fat.
Slice 3 frankfurters.
Saute sliced franks, celery and onion in bacon fat. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add soup and milk.
Cook 10 minutes until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.

title: venison teriyaki
directions: Slice meat diagonally across grain 1/4 inch deep.
Mix rest of ingredients for marinade.
Pour over meat.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lenny's favorite banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and egg yolk.
Add sifted flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add bananas, sour milk and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: honey-barbecued spareribs
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over spareribs and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Uncover after 30 minutes, spooning sauce over ribs until thickened.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes. Recipe may be halved.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cook together as a custard 1 cup sugar, cocoa, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla.
Dissolve baking soda in a little hot water and add to mixture along with remaining 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs, 1 cup milk and flour.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put on your favorite icing.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix with wooden spoon until soft dough forms.
Beat thirty seconds.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until brown.
Combine butter and garlic. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: deep dish chicken pot pie
directions: In a large saucepan; melt margarine, stir in flour, bouillon and pepper. Over medium heat add milk gradually stirring until thickened. Add remaining ingredients except Bisquick. Pour into 2- 1/2 qt. Casserole dish. Prepare Bisquick according to package directions. Roll out to cover top of dish, cutting slits near center. Place dough over filling; turn over edge. Seal and flute. Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown in 375 degree oven.

title: stir-fry shrimp(low-fat)
directions: Spray a nonstick skillet with a nonfat cooking spray.
Add the low calorie spread as needed.
Stir-fry all ingredients, except shrimp, over medium heat until done (about 10 minutes).
Add a combination of soy sauce and water to make a sauce.
Add the shrimp and cook over low heat for a few minutes.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart pan; bring to rolling boil and remove from heat immediately.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Stir well and press into buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: kiwi coolers
directions: Peel kiwis and cut into small pieces.
Place half in a blender with 2 cups of juice and 4 ice cubes.
Blend until smooth, stir in 1 cup sparkling water.
Repeat with the remaining kiwis, 2 cups juice, 4 ice cubes and 1 cup sparkling water. Garnish each serving with a strawberry.
Low-fat.
Serves 8.

title: onion cole slaw
directions: Shred the cabbage very thinly with a sharp knife. Peel and chop
the onions.
Add to cabbage.
Season with salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly the vinegar, salad oil and sugar.
Pour over cabbage mixture.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken in water 45 minutes, then shred meat.
Combine chicken, cheese, onion, green chilies and cream of chicken soup (add 1/2 can milk, using soup can).

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Bake 2 pie shells and let cool.
Pour mixture into pie shells and refrigerate.

title: hidden sloppy joes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Generously grease a 12 cup bundt cake pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes or until peanuts start to pop.
Mix in vanilla, soda and salt.
Stir well. Pour onto well-greased pan or onto a piece of foil.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients.

title: meatball garlic surprise
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except the oil and garlic. Make meatballs each with half garlic clove inside.
Fry until browned.
Drain excess oil.

title: crab spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk, add remaining ingredients and blend.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/3 c. sliced almonds. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Best served with warm miniature rye bread.

title: toast
directions: Put bread in toaster until golden brown.
Spread butter over the top.
Add jam or jelly.
Enjoy.

title: yankee apple john
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch baking dish and fill bottom with sliced apples.
Mix sugar, spices and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Sprinkle over apples.
Sift flour, baking powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix.

title: fruit and cream cheese sticks(appetizers)
directions: Slice cream cheese into small squares and place between pineapple chunks and cherries (secure with fancy toothpicks).
Very easy and colorful; people love them.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together, except crackers, and add broccoli. Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers or buttered Pepperidge Farm mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine (tap sides of pan to distribute crumbs).
Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate and butterscotch pieces.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Sprinkle on pecans and press lightly into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Melt butter in skillet or pan.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Return batter to skillet or pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: heavenly fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water over medium flame until forms hard ball (252°).
Beat egg whites while cooking and pour syrup over egg whites (stiff).
Continue beating until thick enough to drop from spoon onto waxed paper.
Add vanilla and nuts or coconut just before ready to drop (mixture will lose its shine when it is ready).
Food coloring may be added if desired.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Sift together and stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. In small bowl, beat egg.
Add eggnog and oil, then stir into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in the cherries and nuts.
Pour into two well-greased loaf pans (I use Baker's Joy).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove to finish cooling.

title: vegetarian calico beans
directions: Put all ingredients into a pot and cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: streusel strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine baking mix, 1/4 cup melted margarine and milk, mixing until soft dough forms.
Pat dough into two greased 8-inch layer pans.
Combine brown sugar and walnuts.
Cut in remaining margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle evenly over dough.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool.
Cover bottom layer with 1/2 of strawberries and 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Top with second shortcake layer, remaining strawberries and whipped topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together the two whole eggs.
To this mixture, add water, sugar, syrup, melted butter, vanilla and nuts.
Stir thoroughly. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown.
Makes 1 pie.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: pumpkin cream cheese roll
directions: Grease and flour a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice, nutmeg and salt onto wax paper.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix sugar and water together.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Dilute juices according to directions on cans.
Add cooled syrup; mix. Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Makes 35 to 40 servings.

title: apple nut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Use large Bundt or tube pan.

title: sweet-n-sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple juice into large skillet.
Trim pork and cut into 1-inch cubes (like stew meat).
Brown pork in simmering pineapple juice for 5 to 10 minutes, turning frequently.
Peel and slice carrots; add to skillet.
Chop onion and green pepper (including seeds); add to skillet.
Add equal amounts of sugar and vinegar, according to desired flavor strength.
Mix flour and hot water and add to simmering skillet while stirring constantly.
Add pineapple and cook for 5 minutes more.
(Total simmering time depends on how well done you like your vegetables.) Serve over rice.

title: diet peanut butter cookies(32 calories)
directions: Combine banana, egg whites, water, peanut butter, vanilla, raisins and dates in mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Add oats, flour and baking soda.
Mix well.

title: chicken special
directions: Slice chicken breast and marinate it in the cornstarch, soy sauce and white wine or sherry for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese loaf
directions: Combine 3 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Stir.
Combine water, milk and butter in a small saucepan. Heat until warm.
Add to the flour mix.
Add cheese.
Beat at low speed until blended, then beat at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes. Mix in 1 1/2 cups of remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Scrape sides while mixing.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Shape into a ball. Place in a large oiled bowl, turning to bring the oiled side up. Cover with wax paper and a towel.
Let rise for 30 minutes. Grease 2 loaf pans.

title: dilled beans
directions: Wash, string and drain beans; place in large kettle with boiling water and 1 1/2 teaspoons pickling salt.
Boil 20 minutes. Drain.
Save 1 cup liquid.
Combine vinegar, bean liquid and 2 teaspoons pickling salt in kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Pack beans and a pinch of dill and garlic in hot jars; fill with hot vinegar mixture and seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Add cabbage and toss well until coated.

title: festive baked beans
directions: In baking dish, mix beans and fixins and all ingredients listed.
Top with slices of bacon or ham (fat trimmed).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: apple butter
directions: Clean apple butter kettle with salt and vinegar.
