Cook applesauce until it turns reddish.
Add sugar (takes about 1 hour).
Cook 1 hour more.
Seal in jars.
Makes 84 quarts.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, vanilla and salt in medium bowl and beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add flour, sugar and candy and blend well.
Press mixture into 15 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Cover with waxed paper and flatten with rolling pin.
Discard paper.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Cut into squares or let cool and break into pieces.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: mushroom a la creme
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for 2 minutes.
Add sherry and cook another 2 minutes.
Add sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
The consistency of the mix should be that of a rich Hollandaise.
Saturate the golden and very crisp toast with melted butter.
Pour mushroom mix on toast.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves two for lunch.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: jesse's cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Set aside.
Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; then stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: low carb strawberry ice cream
directions: Empty strawberries in food processor. Add Splenda. With processor running, add half and half. Serve immediately.

title: texas hash
directions: Melt shortening in a skillet.
Saute the sliced onions and green peppers until tender.
Add ground beef; cook until there is no pink left in the meat, stirring with a fork to make it crumble. Add tomatoes, rice and seasoning.
Arrange in a 9-inch square baking dish; top with bread crumbs.
Brown slowly in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Combine ingredients together and salt to taste.

title: oriental rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake in a covered casserole dish at 350 degrees for one hour, stirring mixture after 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and pineapple preserves well.
Add vanilla and soda.
Flour the nuts, dates and candied fruit with 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Beat eggs well.
Mix with butter, sugar and preserves.
Add remaining flour to this mixture, then add fruit and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: frozen grape snack
directions: Wash, dry and remove from stem.
Place on pan.
Put in freezer and leave until frozen.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Wash and cut raisins.
Put small amount of flour mixture in paper bag and shake well.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream well.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture alternately with soup.
Stir until smooth; fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch layer pans.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 35 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Slit
chiles
lengthwise on one side.
Remove seeds and drain. Slice
Monterey Jack cheese into 1/4-inch thick slices and place inside chiles.
Place stuffed chiles in an ungreased 3-quart baking
dish.
Mix
eggs, milk, flour, salt and pepper well and pour over chiles.
Sprinkle top with grated Cheddar. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot combination sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buns, in mixing bowl.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut 30 squares of aluminum foil.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order, place foil on cookie sheet.
Do not grease either one.
Put batter on foil by 1/2 teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.
Let cool, then peel off.
These cookies spread out 12 on a sheet.
They are very thin and crisp.
Do not spread dough out, they do that without help.

title: apple tart
directions: To make the crust mix, add the first cup of vegetable oil spread, powdered sugar and vanilla in large bowl of electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Add flour and hazelnuts. Mix well. Press into a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick crust several times with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together ground chuck, oats, onion, salt and pepper.
After well mixed, roll into balls.
To cook meatballs, use crock-pot. Spray with Pam, then pour 1/2 bottle of sweet and sour sauce into crock-pot, place meatballs in sauce, pouring the remaining sauce over meatballs.
Cook in crock-pot on medium 4 to 6 hours until done, then turn on low until ready to eat.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: crazy fudge cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients. Mix until smooth. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add flour and spices to creamed ingredients; mix well.
Then add apples, applesauce, walnuts, raisins and chocolate chips.
Mix in.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: honey fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and honey; add egg, sour milk and flour which has been sifted with soda and salt.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop on greased pans and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: salmon linguini with cheese
directions: On serving platter, combine linguini and Parmesan cheese.
In large skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Cook onion and garlic for 1 minute.
Add peas and carrots, cooking an additional 2 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add dill; reduce heat to medium and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gently fold in salmon and place mixture over linguini.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings; 320 calories per serving.

title: mississippi dutch chicken
directions: Mix all the seasonings.
Add the eggs and milk.
Mix lightly. Add chicken.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Shake flour on chicken. Fry in olive oil.
Drain.
Serve hot.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with Crisco. Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.

title: 7 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: e. g.'s stew meat and potatoes
directions: Fill pressure cooker halfway with water.
Place stew meat, chopped onions and chopped bell pepper in cooker.
Pressure for 20 minutes.
After you finish pressuring, once pressure is released, remove lid.
Place diced potatoes in pressure cooker with meat and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil potatoes and meat until potatoes are done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Stir at least twice.

title: chocolate custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add others and heat well. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Put in pie shell that has been cooked and cooled.
Add meringue and brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzel nuggets; do not overly crush, keep them in small chunks.
Mix pretzels and butter together; pat in bottom of a 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes; let cool.

title: italian dressing for turkey
directions: Combine in a large skillet the oil, onion and bell pepper; brown lightly.
Add ground chuck, garlic salt, all-seasoning salt and black pepper.
Continue to brown lightly over medium heat.
Put ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and Italian stuffing.
Stir while adding celery and its water; mix well.
Add paprika and sage to taste.
Dressing is ready to stuff inside turkey.
Cook in a 325° oven until turkey is done.

title: peach pie
directions: Stir dry ingredients; mix with peaches.
Pour into pastry lined tin.
Cover with top crust with slits for steam to escape. Press edges together, flute and trim.
Bake in quick oven about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 25 minutes longer.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix soups and sour cream together.
Mix chicken and stuffing together and put into baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with 1 teaspoon salt in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Mash potatoes until smooth; add cream cheese, 4 tablespoons butter, garlic salt, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add cream; mix well after each addition. Put in greased baking dish.
(Bake at once or cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.)
Dot top of potatoes with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 325° oven 30 minutes. Increase heat to 375° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese; pour melted margarine over cheese.
Work in flour.
Roll 1/2 inch thick; cut in 1 inch rounds.
Bake on ungreased pan at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(I usually add more flour than recipe calls for.)
Make a roll of dough; pinch off small amount.
Roll into ball and flatten with a fork instead of rolling out and using cutter.
Roll in powdered sugar.
These are nice on a party buffet.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, then put into a shallow, greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate turtle cookies
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and butter and beat.
Add flour and cocoa. Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Heat waffle iron to medium.
Drop by teaspoon on griddle.
Bake 50 seconds.
Ice with chocolate frosting and place 1/2 walnut or pecan on top.
Makes two dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni with almonds according to directions.
Add the diced cooked ham.
Mix all ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese. Layer casserole with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kevin's broccoli dip
directions: Saute the onions, celery and mushrooms in butter.
Cook the broccoli slightly.
Mix broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, cheese and sauteed items.
Heat over low heat and serve hot.

title: peanut delite dessert
directions: Blend flour and margarine together. Add chopped peanuts. Press evenly in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then add peanut butter and beat.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: banana apricot tea bread
directions: Beat together the butter and sugar until creamy and light.

title: beef steak lemon baked
directions: Wipe steak with damp cloth.
Place in baking dish.
Rub with soft butter; season.
Cover with lemon and orange slices.
Combine ketchup, Worcestershire and water and pour over steak.
Cover tightly so meat will steam tender.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread rhubarb in bottom of pan.
Spread marshmallows on top of rhubarb. Put cinnamon candy on marshmallows.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Pour this mixture on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: escarole meatball soup
directions: Mix hamburg, garlic powder, salt, pepper and oregano.
Roll into meatballs the size of a nickel.
Brown lightly in oil; discard oil.
In a 5-quart pot, pour beef broth, carrots, celery, onion, V-8 and meatballs.
Cook over medium-low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
About 15 minutes before soup is ready, add escarole and Romano cheese.
Add macaroni to each bowl when serving.
This will prevent starch build-up in leftover soup.
Makes 6 servings as a meal.
Serve with a hard crusted bread.

title: golden punch
directions: Just before serving, add ginger ale to taste.
Makes approximately 50 cups.
Hint:
If making more than one recipe, freeze one recipe instead of using ice.
Freeze without ginger ale.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel apples; chop in small pieces.
Put in unbaked pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup of sugar and all the cinnamon; pour over apples. Blend 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and margarine; put on top of sugar and cinnamon.
Cover edges of pie shell with foil.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.
Enjoy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix melted butter with stuffing mix and pat 1/2 mixture (or more) into bottom of baking dish.
Set aside.
Stew chicken and debone.
Reserve 1 can chicken broth.
Saute chopped onion and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Layer the chicken on top of stuffing mix.
Pour the heated soup mixture over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: In small bowl, pour boiling water over chocolate.
Let stand 20 minutes to cool.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease well and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour with salt and soda.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil and bean liquid and bring to a boil. Mix beans, pimento and onions.
Put bean mixture into hot liquid. Store in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.

title: porky pot breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain; mix in soup and milk.	Combine with cheese and croutons in casserole.
Beat eggs, 2 c. of milk, and mustard together.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight. Bake one hour at 350°

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let sit for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Toss in cinnamon and sugar.
Melt oleo; pour half into tube or Bundt pan.
Put biscuits in pan. Pour remaining butter over, also leftover cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "christie" cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients in order given.
In medium bowl, mix all dry ingredients; add this to large bowl of mixture.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into golf ball-size balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Do not overbake.
Cookies do not appear to be done.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Cook rutabagas until tender.
Mash rutabagas and spread on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Brown beef and onion.
Spread on top of rutabagas.
Fix mashed potatoes and spread on top of ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine chopped artichokes, Mozzarella, mayo and Parmesan in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine and mix all liquids.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts and dates last.
Pour batter halfway into 4 (one pound) greased coffee cans.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: chilly willy chili(microwave)
directions: Crumble beef into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion and cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until cooked through.
Remove dish from oven.
Stir.
Drain excess grease.
Add beans with juice, stewed tomatoes, chili powder and ketchup.
Cover with lid and microwave on Medium-high for 20 minutes.
Good!

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix in order given:
eggs, sugar, milk, cinnamon and pumpkin. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top. Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: fresh corn salad(very colorful!)
directions: Cook corn in water to cover 5 to 7 minutes or until tender. Drain, cool and set aside.
When cool, remove from ears.
In large bowl, mix oil, vinegar, lemon juice, parsley, sugar, salt, basil and cayenne pepper.
Add corn, tomatoes, onions and green and red pepper to oil mixture.
Mix well.
Chill and cover for several hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, oil and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix together.
Grease and flour your tins. Fill each 1/2 full. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in tins.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar
together.
Beat	in egg. Sift together dry ingredients.
Sprinkle over candy bar pieces and combine
with
creamed mixture.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Pour all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Serves 2.

title: tropical whirl(breakfast drink)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until well blended. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients.
Add and mix dry ingredients.
Drop and flatten onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 11 minutes.

title: hello dollie cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over the melted butter and press down.
Sprinkle on the other ingredients.
Pour milk evenly over all.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cherry cheese delight
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Place raisins and hot water in a small bowl; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients except last three.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water; add to batter.
Mix well.
Drain softened raisins and fold into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
If desired, dust top with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredient in blender, process until smooth.
Makes 1 1/4 cups or 1 can.
Can be made a little ahead to use during busy holiday cooking.

title: cheesy ham scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of the ham in a 2-quart casserole which has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover with half of the potatoes and half of the onion.
Sift half of the flour over and sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Repeat layering ham, potatoes, onion, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour milk over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° in oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover.
Combine bread crumbs and melted oleo.
Sprinkle atop casserole.
Add shredded cheese on top and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves approximately 6 people.

title: lemon marmalade
directions: Remove any seeds from the lemons.
Discard end pieces.
In a large heavy saucepan, combine the lemons, lemon rind and water. Bring to a boil.
Boil rapidly, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in sugar; cook rapidly, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Place a small amount of mixture in a spoon.
Cool slightly.
The mixture should "sheet" from the spoon or drop off more or less as a single drop. If using a candy thermometer, it should read 228° when marmalade is ready.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jar and seal with lid or paraffin (first cooling the marmalade to point of setting before sealing).

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, heat pineapple with juice and sugar; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Mix cornstarch paste to pineapple mixture.
Cool until thick.
Meanwhile, mix cream cheese until smooth; add evaporated milk and pudding powder.
Mix until blended, mixture will be thick.
Add Cool Whip and blend well. Then add pineapple mixture to pudding mixture; blend well.
Pour into pie crust and chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: broccoli and rice casserole(a quick and easy side dish for all occasions)
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Stir.
Add rice and broccoli.
Mix.
Cook in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: queso flameado
directions: Brown sausage in a small skillet; remove to paper towels with slotted spoon.
Drain all but 1 teaspoon drippings from skillet. Add onion; cook until tender.
Return sausage to skillet.
Add tomatoes and picante sauce; simmer for 15 minutes, or until most of liquid is gone.
In a 9-inch baking dish, arrange 2 cups of the cheese.
Top with sausage mixture; cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Garnish with avocado and tomato slices.
Serve immediately with warm tortillas or tortilla chips.

title: orange tapioca jello
directions: Mix together dry ingredients of Jell-O and pudding. Add 3 cups hot water including juice from oranges. Heat until thick and comes to a boil. Cool. Fold in Cool Whip and oranges. Chill.

title: waldorf fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Serve on a lettuce leaf if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: imitation crab meat casserole
directions: Cube crab meat, Velveeta cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Cook soup with milk and melt in both cheeses.
Arrange crab meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over crab meat.
Crush 8 to 10 Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top.
Dab with butter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour melted margarine over sugar in a bowl.
Beat eggs well and pour over sugar and margarine.
Add buttermilk, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well with a spoon.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until tops are golden brown.

title: pumpkin punch surprise
directions: All of the ingredients need to be cold when mixed together. Combine and chill apple juice and pumpkin pie mix.
Just before serving, combine this mixture with the ice cream; stir.
Add the soda.
Yields 4 1/4 quarts.

title: mary's cherry angel treat
directions: In large mixing bowl, gradually add powdered sugar to cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream, add cake (broken in small pieces).
Spread into large cake pan.
Add cherries on top.
Cover and chill at least 2 to 3 hours.
Even better made the day before serving.

title: one-two-three-four cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with the milk. Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers at 375° for 25 minutes.
Can be used for cupcakes.

title: gourmet meat balls
directions: Cook onion in butter until yellow and transparent on low heat. Pour milk over bread crumbs and allow to stand until milk has been absorbed.
Beat with a fork to a smooth mass.
Add beef, onion, salt and mix only until blended.
Form into small balls and brown in 10-inch skillet.
No fat needed.
Combine sour cream and chili sauce and pour over the meat balls.
Reduce heat and simmer gently for 10 minutes, turning meat balls once or twice as they cook.

title: tomato fritters
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except butter. Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Heat
butter in skillet and drop in fritters by the spoonful.
Fry to golden brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Brown hamburger meat and drain. Put in large baking dish.
Chop onion and spread over meat.
Add soups and cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen before cooking.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Mix marinade and place pork loin in refrigerator 24 to 48 hours.
Place pork loin and marinade in casserole.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake at 350° until done.
Save baked marinade for topping.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wrap each chicken breast in ham.
Place in casserole dish.
Pat each piece with a little butter.
Mix sour cream with mushroom soup.
Spread over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix everything together and put dough into refrigerator for 1 hour. Roll out on floured board and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes until light brown.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place butter in baking dish and melt in oven.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into melted butter in baking dish. Do not stir.
Add fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven until crust forms over top and becomes golden brown.
May top with ice cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix banana, sugar, egg and butter.
Mix flour, salt & baking soda; add to banana mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 325 degrees for 55-60 minutes.

title: roasted quail
directions: Pick, singe, draw and wipe 6 quail.
Cut the head off and stuff them with stewed prunes, stewed apples or mashed and seasoned, mashed potatoes.
Lay a strip of bacon over each breast. Put them in a roasting pan and spread a little butter over each quail.
Dust with salt; let cook in oven for 18 minutes.
Place on toast; garnish with watercress or lettuce.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add cold water.
Chill until it starts to set up.
Add Equal to yogurt and fold into Jell-O.
Whip by hand until smooth.
Add oranges and chill. Contains 45 calories.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix in shredded zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in greased and floured pan(s). Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken
in
flour,
fry
in
skillet until golden brown. Remove
chicken
and
set	aside in same skillet;	add soup, onion,
thyme
and	celery	flakes,
salt
and
pepper. Gradually add water,	bring
to
a
boil, stirring constantly. Pour rice in shallow casserole.	Stir in all except 1/3 cup of soup mixture. Top
with
chicken, pour remaining soup mixture over chicken. Cover with	aluminum foil.	Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until chicken
is
tender.
Sprinkle
with parsley flakes for show.

title: oatmeal apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, 1 tablespoon flour and sugar.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients; sprinkle on top of apple mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add sugar, then milk and oleo.
Mix well.
Put in Pyrex baking dish; put can of peaches on top of mixture.
DO NOT STIR. Cinnamon can be used on top.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and soda that has been sifted together.
Alternate 3 times with the mixture and the mashed bananas.
Bake in a 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.

title: noni's celery mushroom casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water until tender.
Fry mushrooms in a little butter for 5 minutes; add peas and soup and heat well.
Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: slo-cooker chili
directions: Brown ground beef on range top.
Put into slo-cooker.
Add onion, green peppers, garlic, tomatoes, kidney beans, salt, chili powder, pepper and cumin.
Stir to combine.
Cover and simmer at setting No. 2 1/2 for 7 to 10 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy rigatoni
directions: Cook rigatoni according to package; drain.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and parsley.
Add butter.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until butter is melted and sauce is heated through.
Stir in rigatoni. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in 2 eggs and vanilla.
In small bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes. Remove from oven.
Run knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pack into an ungreased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix all together; store in airtight container.

title: squash casserole
directions: In
a
saucepan cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for
minutes;
drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and
sour cream.
Stir
in
shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash
and onion.
Combine
stuffing mix and butter.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture
in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining
stuffing
over vegetables.
Bake
at
for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Combine celery seed, chili powder, sugar, salt and paprika. Rub 1/3 of the mixture on ribs. To remaining mixture, add tomato sauce and vinegar.
Heat and use to baste ribs. Cook over hot coals until tender, basting occasionally with the sauce.

title: marinated shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse and drain.
Drain and soak shrimp as label directs.
In small jar with tight fitting lid, combine oil, lemon juice and salad dressing; mix.
Shake well.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss with dressing.
Cover; chill several hours.
Serve with paprika.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Beat well. Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Add nuts and stir well.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Add a can of cream of mushroom soup and simmer until smooth.
Add spaghetti which has been cooked in chicken broth.

title: naples pie
directions: Empty coconut into a greased pie pan.
Add soft butter or margarine, mix and pat coconut into the sides and bottom of a pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (until slightly browned).

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown beef with onion and bell pepper; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and pork and beans.
Stir and simmer on top of stove for 15 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, reserving juice. Add enough water to juice to make 2/3 cup liquid. Combine dry ingredients. Add reserved juice; mix well. Melt butter in baking dish. Pour batter into dish and spoon peaches over batter. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pudding mixture
directions: Add dry ingredients to pudding mixture.
Add milk.
Cook, then add vanilla.

title: snack squares
directions: Melt marshmallows, peanut butter and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add cereal, oats and raisins; mix well.
Press mixture firmly into greased 8-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into 16 squares.

title: fruit compote
directions: Beat 1 can cranberry sauce; thin with fruit juices.
Mix with cut up fruit pieces in a bowl.

title: crab dip
directions: Put cream cheese on serving plate.
Drain crab meat and put on top of cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce on top of crab meat.

title: zucchini sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown sausage, breaking into small pieces.
Drain.
Toss with 1 tablespoon flour; spread on bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
In same skillet, cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Remove from heat; toss with remaining flour.
Spoon half the zucchini mixture over meat.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate and paraffin. Form in 1-inch balls and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and let cool on wax paper.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix and sift the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream the shortening.
Add the sugars gradually and cream thoroughly. Add the eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine syrup, buttermilk, pumpkin, nuts and vanilla.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the flour mixture, stirring after each addition until
barely smooth. Grease only the bottom of a loaf pan; line with waxed paper and pour in the batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Yield:
1 beautiful cake.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour and dry ingredients, then add to Crisco.
Mix with pastry blender or fork until mealy.
Add liquid and knead lightly a few times to mix.
Let stand 15 minutes.
After 15 minutes, roll thin.
Cut in strips about 2 1/2 inches long, or as desired.
Great for any kind of good broth.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and let rise.
When ready to cook, stir, then drop into hot grease until brown and float to the top of the oil. Drain on paper towels and serve.
The dough needs to be thick. Use a small amount of milk or water to make it the right consistency.

title: passion pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles and peppers. Add sugar and let set overnight, covered.
Place in jars or sealed containers and refrigerate.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: *Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over 3 slices of bread and brown crumbs.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix and beat ingredients for 4 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.
The cake should shake like pudding when it comes out of oven, but be firm in middle; toothpick test.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding on stove according to directions for pudding on box.
Turn off heat.
Add peanut butter to taste.
Pour in a graham cracker crust.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Heat the olive oil in a heavy skillet.
Add the beans and cook, stirring and tossing constantly until beans are about half cooked and become bright green.
Reduce heat and add garlic and onion.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, parsley, vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper and continue to cook, tossing occasionally for about another 5 minutes or until sauce is slightly reduced.
Serve immediately or cool and serve at room temperature.
Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine margarine and shortening.
Add sugar one cup at a time.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over dates; let cool and drain.
Brown oatmeal in oven on cookie sheet.
Cream shortening; add egg and sweetener and beat well.
Add combined dry ingredients (oatmeal, flour, soda, spices and nuts).
Add remaining ingredients (bananas and dates) and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Allow to cool slightly while chopping other ingredients.
Layer in large bowl the hamburger, onion, tomatoes, beans, cheese, lettuce and chips.

title: munching onion dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Miracle Whip; mix well until blended. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: supper boats
directions: Cut bread in half the long way.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Spread mixture on bread.
Put bread on foil and fold foil up on sides of bread.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
To serve, slice and dip in spaghetti sauce.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until it spins a thread when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until thick.
Pour syrup slowly over egg whites beating continually until about half the syrup is used.
Set back over heat while you scrape the sides of the bowl to mix ingredients well.
Pour rest of syrup over mixture while still beating.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat candy until it will hold its shape.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Can be poured into buttered pan and cut into squares when cool.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: roll-ups
directions: Trim round steak, cutting into approximately 3-inch wide strips.
Pound meat until it is flat and thin.
Salt and pepper and cover each strip with slice of potato and onion.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer vegetables one package at a time.
Mix 1/2 pound shredded or sliced cheese (cut up), 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup, 1 small can condensed milk and pimento for color.
Pour over the layered vegetables.

title: dream salad
directions: Place jello, sugar, pineapple juice and water in a double boiler or a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add marshmallows to hot liquid.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Cool completely.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, nuts and Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.

title: spanish rice and chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine garlic salt, celery salt and paprika; sprinkle over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan. Combine rice, onion, green pepper and parsley; spoon into the pan.
In a saucepan, bring broth, tomatoes, salt and chili powder to a boil.
Pour over rice mixture; mix well.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a large bowl.
Add apples and toss gently.
Stir in beaten egg and margarine.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
(For firmer crust, brush first with egg white.)
If desired, may sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 minutes or until it quits shaking.
Check after 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Saute onion until golden brown in a little fat.
Mix all ingredients together with only enough water to help in forming balls.
Brown balls in same fat as onions were browned in, turning frequently to brown uniformly.
Add 1/2 cup hot water.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Makes about 24 meatballs.

title: super meat loaf(microwave)
directions: In a bowl mix the first seven ingredients.
Shape mixture on the roast rack in a 2-quart oblong dish.
Score the top with diagonal 1/2-inch valleys.
Combine brown sugar, dry mustard and catsup.
Spoon and spread over top of meat.
Microwave uncovered on High for 12 to 14 minutes, rotating dish once.
Remove and cover meat with waxed paper.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup (Karo) until threads.
Add butter and peanuts.
Cook slowly to 300°.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
(Stir quickly because it foams up.) Spread onto 2 greased cookie sheets.
When cool, break into smaller pieces.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: chicken roll-up
directions: Boil the chicken breasts until tender; debone.
Divide the breasts in halves so there are 8.
Take a package of 8 crescent dinner rolls.
Roll out and lay pieces of chicken and sliced Velveeta cheese on top.
Roll up.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown rolls in 400° oven.
Take out.
Warm the soup and 1/2 can of milk.
Pour over the chicken breasts.
Put back in the oven and heat until the mixture bubbles.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir soup mix and sour cream until blended.
Cover; chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: grape hull pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add grape hulls and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 400° until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: blueberry oatmeal bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine with pastry cutter until mixture resembles coarse meal. Combine eggs, milk and corn syrup; mix well.
Add to the dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaf in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar, in a bowl. Chill dough 1 hour. Roll balls in powdered sugar and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease large Bundt pan.
Mix granulated sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over bottom of pan.
Tear each biscuit into fourths.
(Open only one can at a time).
Roll each biscuit piece in the sugar mixture.
Melt margarine and add brown sugar.
Mix well and simmer for 1 minute.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot balls
directions: Put all ingredients through food processor or food grater. Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in blender. Add half and half to blender. Dump mixture into ice cream maker container. Add whipping cream and add whole milk to the container to the fill line (do not overfill). Add vanilla. Insert beater to container. Manually turn back and forth so mixture blends together. Ice cream maker will stop when ice cream is done.

title: salmon roll
directions: Combine salmon, cream cheese and Worcestershire and mix well. Shape into ball or log.
Roll in mixture of pecans and parsley. Roll up in plastic wrap or wax paper.
Chill to blend flavors. Serve with crackers.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: cabbage sausage soup
directions: In Dutch oven or saucepan, brown sliced sausages.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Set sausages aside.
Add cabbage and onion to drippings.
Cook over medium heat until lightly browned, about 7 minutes.
Add carrots and chicken broth. Cover; simmer about 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add pepper and sausages.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 9 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: ribbon salad
directions: May add chopped tomatoes just before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey dipped chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs and honey.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Wash chicken pieces.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Heat shortening in deep skillet on medium heat. Dip chicken pieces in batter, only as much as you can fry.
Brown well on both sides, frying slowly.
Turn occasionally, 15 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn occasionally while baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frosted flakes cookies
directions: Measure flakes, then crush to 1 1/2 cups; set aside.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add flour mixture; mix good.
Add Frosted Flakes (crushed).
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Blend together broccoli, soup, mayonnaise and 1 package shredded cheese.
Spread this mixture in baking pan with mixture 1 1/2-inches deep in pan.
Sprinkle the other package cheese over top.
